title: coconut icing
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a small saucepan.
Heat to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Boil mixture until a small amount of mixture spins a 6 to 8-inch thread when dropped from a spoon.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Cut chicken in strips 1/2-inch wide.
Place chicken in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover dish with lid or vented plastic wrap. Microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring twice.
Remove chicken from casserole and set aside.
Discard juices.
In same casserole, combine green pepper and next 4 ingredients.
Cover dish and microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring once. Drain if desired.
Combine gravy, soy sauce and ginger.
Stir into vegetables.
Return chicken to casserole.
Add pineapple.
Cover dish and microwave at High for 4 to 5 minutes, until thoroughly heated, stirring twice.
Serve chicken over cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Cook spinach until tender, drain.
Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole dish (flat, such as 7 x 11-inch).
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour, or until middle is set.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix up real well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions, add salt
& pepper.
Add mushroom soup.
Spread this in bottom of casserole dish.
Then layer of cheese and top with cream of chicken soup.
Do not heat soup just spread it right out of can, then top with remaining cheese.
Layer tater tots on top.
Bake till taters are brown at 350°.

title: egg in toast
directions: Cut a hole in the middle of the bread.
Use a glass or biscuit cutter.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a frying pan.
Put in the bread and crack the egg into the hole.
Cook until bread is golden brown on the bottom.
Turn bread egg over.
Put 1 tablespoon butter in pan; continue frying until the egg looks done.
Enjoy!

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Saute bacon until crisp.
Add chopped veggies.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add garlic, 1 teaspoon cumin and other spices.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add beans, ham hocks and broth.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove ham hocks; pick over and return meat to pot.
Add rest of cumin, cayenne and lime juice at end.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil, then add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add the rest of ingredients to mixture and mix well. Bake 40 minutes at 325° in three greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups milk on low heat while mixing sugar, egg yolks, cornstarch, cocoa and 1/2 cup milk.
Add to warm milk; when thick, add flavoring and margarine, cook another 2 minutes until blended well.
Place in cooked pie shell; add meringue, bake about 15 minutes at 375° or until meringue is browned to your liking.

title: pancake topping
directions: Put water, cornstarch, coffee, cinnamon and salt into saucepan.
Stir while cooking until clear and slightly thickened. Remove from heat and add maple, vanilla, Sugar Twin and margarine. Can be used anytime; best when warm.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add grits to water slowly. Cook until water is absorbed (be careful it spits at you).
Take from heat.
Add oleo, cheese and hot sauce. Stir to dissolve cheese and oleo.
Beat in the eggs. Pour into buttered casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in medium oven.

title: microwave honey corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, biscuit mix and baking powder in large bowl.
Add milk, eggs, honey and oil.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 8-inch square microproof baking dish.
Cook on 50 for 10 minutes.
Rotate dish if bread seems to be rising unevenly.
Cook on High 2 to 4 minutes or until bread tests done. Remove and let stand 5 minutes; serve warm.
Makes 8 servings. Cooking time is 12 to 14 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, salt, soy sauce and 3/4 of the pineapple liquid.
Cook until clear and slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add meat, peppers, onions and pineapple chunks.
Cook about 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: raspberry gelatin salad
directions: Mix raspberry Jell-O, 3 cups hot water and 1 cup cold water. Add crushed pineapple (including juice).
Add raspberries.
Pour half of this mixture into gelatin mold.
Let set.
Spread sour cream on top.
Set an hour.
Add remaining half of gelatin mixture.

title: quiche muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 muffin pans.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, garlic salt, white pepper and dill, and set aside.
In large bowl of mixer, combine grated vegetables, cheese, milk, oil, bread crumbs and eggs.
Mix together to blend; add the flour mixture and mix just to combine.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full of batter and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 18 muffins.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Heat shortening and molasses to boiling point.
Take from heat and stir in 2 cups flour while hot.
Let cool.
Add soda, dissolved in vinegar.
Beat eggs and ginger together.
Knead with about 3 cups flour to roll out nicely.
If the dough is chilled somewhat it will not require as much flour to roll out and cookies will be softer.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook chopped potatoes, onion, celery and broccoli until soft and tender.
(Barely cover with water while cooking.) Place in blender and blend.
Pour in heavy saucepan.
Add milk and make a paste of 1 tablespoon flour and 2 tablespoons milk to thicken. Heat slowly but do not boil.
Yields 4 servings.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add sugar, soda and shortening. Stir until shortening is soft.
Crumble yeast into mixture; stir well.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into mixture and mix well.
Let dough stand on floured board for 10 minutes.
Knead lightly and make into rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until browned.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: new potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water (with cover) for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and let cool.
Peel potatoes and slice into 1/2-inch slices.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Blend sour cream with sugar, vanilla and melted butter.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to first mixture blending well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spoon into greased eight inch pan and bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake as directed on box.
Be sure to cook in a very large sheet pan because you need a lot of space on top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Add all ingredients to a large mixing bowl and mix very well.
Bake until cake tests done.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Add pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until chilled (overnight).
Let set out of refrigerator before serving, if too hard.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Mix together sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery seed and paprika.
Dip chicken into the sour cream mixture, then into stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and Pet milk together.
Pour into container and fill with milk to the full line.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until done.

title: banana cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Stir in bananas and buttermilk.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt and stir in cream mixture.
Blend in nuts.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: dutch baked corn
directions: Melt butter with flour; pour milk in gradually.
Bring to a boil; add corn, seasonings and the egg yolks (well beaten).
Fold in egg whites (beaten stiff).
Put in a buttered, greased casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi d'amour
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and gently fry the garlic, onion and tomato.
Be sure the liquid is out of pan before adding cream.
Add heavy cream and simmer to reduce liquid to sauce consistency.
Add almonds, paprika and salt and pepper.
Poach the shrimp in the sauce for approximately 3 minutes.
Stir in Amaretto and serve over fine linguine or angel hair pasta.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw vegetables; beat eggs and melt butter.
Mix all together in medium casserole (minus 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
During last 15 minutes, put rest of Cheddar on top to melt.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Take meat off bone.
Cut into pieces.
Mix meat with remaining ingredients.
Pour in 12 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix well and cook in double boiler until thick.
Put in two (bought) crusts that have been cooked.
Top with meringue (beaten egg whites) and brown lightly in oven.

title: crawfish soup
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients over medium heat.
Stir often.
Add remaining ingredients, except sherry.
Heat to serving temperature. Stir in sherry just before serving.
Serves Four.

title: yogurt garlic dressing(lo-fat)
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and blend well with a whisk.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Pour into 9 X 9 greased pan. Add fruit. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel coated popcorn and peanuts
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, Karo and oleo.
Bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Immediately stir in soda.
Remove from stove and pour over mixed popcorn and peanuts.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Place in a 200° oven.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: tangy fruit
directions: Whisk together pudding mix, Tang and reserved pineapple juice. Toss with fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; add flour and chocolate chips. Stir.
Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine all ingredients and place in a buttered 2-1/2 quart casserole. Bake covered for 1-1/2 to 2 hours.

title: green bean and ham casserole
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a buttered casserole dish. Mix soup, milk and flour; pour over top. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour, then 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt butter and put in a jelly roll pan.
Top butter with a mixture of the brown sugar & cinnamon.
Mix milk and eggs.	Dip slices of bread on both sides into egg mixture, put in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.	Invert out of pan immediately when done.	(Can be refrigerated overnight before baking.)	Best if you line the jelly roll pan with tinfoil first, for easy clean-up.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump peaches and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Cut margarine into 1/4-inch slices and spread evenly over dry mix.
Nuts may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 12 servings.

title: oven fries italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line baking pan with foil.
Spray heavy with cooking spray.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1/2 inch wedges. Melt butter.
In a large bowl, combine oil, garlic, butter and spices.
Add potatoes.
Toss around to coat.
Arrange in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn twice. Should be tender and golden.

title: marinated shrimp and pasta salad
directions: In small jar, mix oil, lemon juice, salad dressing and horseradish.
Mix well.
In large bowl, combine pasta and all other ingredients.
Toss with dressing.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla, water and 1/2 cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.

title: punch
directions: Boil 3 cups water
and
5 cups sugar.
Take off heat and add the rest except
the ginger ale.
Can make ahead and put in the refrigerator.
Put ginger ale in last just before serving.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Heat rice, mushrooms, seasoning, onions, broth and butter. Pour into a 3-quart oblong casserole; stir in almonds.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir well before serving. Great!!!

title: reuben chicken
directions: Put chicken in roasting pan.
Top each chicken breast with drained sauerkraut and Swiss cheese.
Pour Thousand Island dressing over all chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil and put under broiler for a few seconds.

title: tuna shrimp casserole
directions: Mix in order given, folding tuna and shrimp in last.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: spicy mexican chicken
directions: Put flour in a bag.
Shake one piece of chicken at a time in the bag to coat.
Heat 4 tablespoons oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat and saute the chicken 15 minutes until lightly browned on both sides.
Set chicken pieces aside.
Add remaining oil to skillet and saute peppers and onion until tender.
Add cinnamon, cloves, chili powder, garlic, peanuts, broth and oregano.
Heat until simmering.
Spoon out 1/2 cup of sauce and blend with cornstarch.
Return this mixture to casserole and simmer until sauce thickens.
Add chicken pieces to sauce; cover and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with pepper and serve.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water in bowl.
Sprinkle on yeast and stir until it looks soft.
Add salt, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Knead dough (press down, fold over and press down again) for 5 to 10 minutes.
Roll and shape dough into anything you want.
Lay pretzels on cookie sheet.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with salt, cinnamon, sugar, etc.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover top of casserole with Pepperidge Farm bread dressing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in large bowl.
In saucepan, combine margarine, water, shortening and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend. Pour in 12 x 18-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 22 minutes or a little more at 400°.

title: brown flour potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and cook with onion until tender.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Brown flour in melted butter in heavy frypan, stirring constantly.
When well browned, stir into the soup and cook until thickened.
Season to taste.
Add eggs.

title: southern ice cream-grits
directions: Cook the grits in salt water.
Add butter and grated cheese. Beat eggs and milk together and add to grits.
Pour into a buttered casserole and bake at 350° from 55 to 60 minutes.

title: berry delight
directions: Wash and dry blueberries.
Place half the berries in the pie shell.
Melt jelly over low heat and pour it over the blueberries. Cover top of jelly with sour cream.
Top with remaining blueberries.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: seven layer vegetable and meat casserole
directions: Saute onions and ground beef in skillet seasoned with salt and pepper until meat is brown.
Set aside.
In greased casserole, place in layers potatoes, sauteed beef, carrots, celery, zucchini, green peppers and mushroom.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pickled squash
directions: Place garlic and dill seed
in
jars.
Slice
squash and pack in jars.
Bring vinegar, salt
and water to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over squash.
Seal.
Process
in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 pints.

title: microwave pretty potato salad
directions: Break eggs into
a 1 quart casserole; pierce yolks with a fork.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Cook, covered, on Full power 1 minute
and
seconds
to
minute and 45 seconds until eggs
are
cooked.
Let
cool, then finely chop. Add remaining
ingredients.
Toss.
Chill several hours before serving.
Garnish with
parsley
and tomato wedges.
Yields 12 (1-cup) servings with 55 calories per serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and pour over crumbs.
Mix well and pack on bottom of pan or dish.
Beat at least 15 minutes in mixer 1 stick oleo, 2 eggs and 2 cups powdered sugar.
Pour mixture over crumbs and cover completely.
Layer rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Sprinkle with nuts and decorate with cherries.
Let set 4 hours or overnight in icebox.

title: herb stuffed shrimp
directions: Rinse shrimp and pat dry.
With a sharp knife, cut along the channel where the vein was removed.
Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly grease 4 individual gratin dishes or a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix together the bread crumbs, garlic, thyme, parsley, butter, hot pepper sauce and lemon juice until well blended.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Open each shrimp so the cut edges spread out slightly (butterfly).
Fill the curve of the shrimp with some stuffing.
Place shrimp, stuffing side up in the prepared dishes. Sprinkle the remaining stuffing over the top.
Bake 15 minutes or until the shrimp is opaque and the stuffing is golden.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for almonds. Roll out and sprinkle almonds on top. Bake in oven until lightly browned.

title: cheesy eggplant pie
directions: Make pie crusts; bake at 450°.
Partially cook eggplant in salt water.
Drain.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour.
Stir in soup, oregano and pepper.
Heat, while stirring, until bubbly.
Stir 1/2 of mixture in beaten eggs, then return all to saucepan.
Fold in tomato, cheese and eggplant. Pour into crusts and arrange crust cuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: smothered hamburger steaks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; shape into 6 patties. Cook patties in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat 3 minutes on each side. Remove patties from skillet. Add onion and 1/4 cup water to skillet; cook, covered, over medium heat for 15 minutes. Uncover and stir; cook 10 more minutes. Remove half of onion from skillet. Return patties to skillet. Top patties with reserved onion; cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Preheat deep fryer filled half full of oil.
Drain all but 1/4 cup of liquid off the salmon or tuna and set that aside.
Then put the salmon or tuna in a mixing bowl and break it apart with a fork until you have no big flakes.
Add the flour and egg.
You can use a dash of pepper, but no salt.
Mix well.
Add the baking powder to the liquid that was set aside and beat well with a fork or whisk until frothy (this is an important step, and this mixture can't "sit").
Pour into the fish and stir until well blended. Scoop out a teaspoonful of the mixture at a time, using another teaspoon to push the mixture off the spoon and into the deep fryer of hot oil.
Watch the "salmon/tunaettes" closely because they brown quickly.
Lift out with a slotted spoon and place in a paper towel.
Serve and enjoy.

title: ice cream custard
directions: Mix eggs, add sugar, salt and flour well.
Add milk.
Cook in a thick, heavy pan on the stove until thickens.
Cook on low temperature and keep stirring so it won't stick.
Makes a good homemade ice cream.
Add favorite flavoring and freeze in freezer.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Melt margarine in skillet, add mushrooms and zucchini.	Saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and garlic.
Pour into small casserole dish, top with croutons, sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes or until cheese is completely melted.

title: mexican enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole; set aside.
In large skillet, cook meat, onion and garlic in oil over medium heat until meat is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Heat over medium heat until bubbly.
Reduce heat to very low; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Mix Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack cheese and set aside.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk and cook to soft ball.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Put into a 9 x 12-inch pan and cool.

title: bacon burger squares
directions: Cook bacon until almost done, but not crisp.
Cut bacon slices in half crosswise.
Pat beef into a 12 x 6-inch rectangle; cut into 8 squares.
Combine lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Brush over patties.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange in a greased wire grill basket.
Place 2 half slices of bacon crisscross on top of each burger.
Close basket.
Grill burgers over medium-hot coals until desired cooking time, turning often.
Allow about 20 minutes total time for medium.
Serve on buns.
Makes 8 servings.

title: original girl scout cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll on a heavily floured board until very thin.
Cut out with a 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.
Yields 30 cookies.

title: cantaloupe strawberry sundae
directions: Have melon well chilled.
Cut in half and scoop out seeds. Fill each half with ice milk.
Puree or blend strawberries with sweetener and orange juice and spoon over ice milk.
Serve immediately. Serves 2.

title: orange crush cake
directions: Mix well all ingredients at once. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake 2 hours.

title: bev's chocolate icebox pie
directions: Place in top of double boiler and melt.
When cool add 1/2 pint cream, whipped.
Place in graham cracker crust and put in icebox until ready to use.

title: christmas figure cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and continue to beat until light. Add well beaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and creamed; mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Roll thin to 1/8-inch on lightly floured board and cut with cookie cutter or form drop cookies.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown onion and meat; drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 10 minutes or longer.
Have grated cheese, chopped lettuce, tomato and onions.
Spoon sauce over Fritos.
Add salad ingredients and taco sauce to taste.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl mix 1/4 cup of soup, beef, bread crumbs, eggs and onion.
Shape into 6 patties.
Fry in skillet until browned on both sides.
Spoon out fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms. Return patties to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done.

title: cauliflower-broccoli casserole
directions: Steam cauliflower and broccoli buds.
Fry sliced onions and mushrooms in pan.
In a greased casserole dish, put cauliflower, broccoli, onions and mushrooms.
Drain and add 1 can stewed tomatoes.
Spoon on Cheddar cheese soup.
Dot with oleo.
Place in 300° oven for 30 minutes to heat through.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy. Add flour and banana, beating until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat salad dressing, cake mix, eggs, water and cinnamon at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Spread with frosting or sprinkle powdered sugar over top of cooled cake.

title: freezer corn
directions: Combine in large pot; simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Pour in large container to cool.
Put in freezer bags.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare and cut potatoes into quarters.
Combine flour, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Dip potatoes in melted butter, then roll in flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: rotel chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken; keep broth.
Cook spaghetti.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add to spaghetti.
Add chicken to mixture, then Ro-Tel.
Last, add the Velveeta.
Let all the mixture simmer for 25 minutes on low heat.
Good with crackers, garlic bread or rolls.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Pour in an unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until center is done.

title: caramel crunch apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Roll pastry to 12-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Place in 9-inch pie pan; turn under edge and flute.
Melt caramels with water over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Spoon apples into crust; top with caramel sauce.
Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add cream of tartar, flour, flavoring and coconut.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a greased, floured pan.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together the mayonnaise, dash lemon juice, cheese and soup.
Layer chicken, broccoli, and cheese mixture.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbles and top is browned.
Approximately 30 minutes.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Combine cake mix with coconut and rub in butter until mixture resembles fine bread crumbs.
Press into a well-greased slab tin, 12 x 8-inch, coming about 1/2-inch up the sides.
Slab pan can be lined with foil and greased, if preferred.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine jello, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll in red sugar on the sides and dip end in green sugar.

title: mini bit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in separate bowl.
Mix sugars, eggs, vanilla and butter until creamy. Mix in flour mixture.
Stir in mini bits.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets.
Bake until golden brown.

title: layered stuffed cabbage
directions: In frying pan, add uncooked rice and ground round and brown. Mix in a bowl the tomato sauce, 1 can of water, can of tomatoes with its juice, salt and pepper. Shred cabbage to size of your liking. In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, put a layer of cabbage, a
layer of meat mix and a layer of tomato sauce. Repeat until all is used. Top with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 25 minutes).
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add milk and Wesson oil.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add flavoring and beat 1 minute.
Fold in coconut and pour into tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine chicken, onion, celery and bell pepper with water. Season to taste.
When chicken is done, bone and cube.
Save liquid.
Mix 2 cans soup with cheese, chicken, vegetables and some of broth.
Add cooled spaghetti and pimento to mixture.
Place in casserole.
Place breadcrumbs on top.
Warm and eat.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Chop onion, pepper and celery.
Mix with beans, ketchup and mustard.
Top with brown sugar.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat both sides of chicken with flour mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet.
Add remaining margarine, mushrooms, onions and parsley.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Stir in what is left of flour mixture and blend in wine.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Add chicken, reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Turn chicken occasionally to baste.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole soup
directions: Combine soup and water in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add pepper, onion, rice, shrimp and hot sauce.
Heat, stirring.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar and melt just before serving.

title: becky's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: carole mcmann's summer salad
directions: Put Cool Whip into a bowl. Mix in Jell-O. When blended, add cottage cheese. Add orange sections and pineapple. Mix well and chill before serving.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with vegetables.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in milk, sugar, flour and nutmeg. Stir in rhubarb.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Dot with butter. Make several slits in top crust for air vents.
Bake at 450°
for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes longer.

title: nanny's sweet potato rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, sweet potatoes and half the flour.
Mix in remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place, greased side up, in greased bowl.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round baking pans or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.
In large mixer bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans (35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pans or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean).
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Frost with 1 bowl buttercream frosting.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: ranch cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes approximately 30 bars.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Take out 2 to 3 hours before you need; then add 7-Up or ginger ale before you serve.
(Plastic milk jugs work great to freeze punch in.)

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix together and spread in greased 9 x 13 pan.	Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. This will not look done, but remove and cool.

title: party time salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point; add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese.
Add to gelatin mixture and blend.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts. Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: baked chicken
directions: Take the soup and cover all the chicken.
Then cover with aluminum foil and bake about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
When chicken cools, take it out of soup, take it off the bone, tear in small pieces and put back into soup.
Cook noodles until done; drain. Mix with chicken and soup.

title: spaghetti pizza deluxe
directions: Prepare spaghetti as package directs.
Drain.
In medium bowl, blend milk and egg.
Add spaghetti and toss to coat.
Spray 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with cooking spray.
Spread spaghetti mixture evenly in pan.

title: stroganoff casserole
directions: Press unrolled crescent dough on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan to form thin pastry.
In skillet brown beef and onion; season with paprika, salt and pepper.
Mix in mushrooms and sour cream.
Spread warm over pastry and top with cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 minutes or until pastry is baked.
Cut in squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Mix strawberries with 1 cup sugar.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: party pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar added with salt and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
When very stiff, spread on buttered 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Should not brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, butter and sugar.
Add vanilla. Thoroughly mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yummy!

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine 2 packages jello with boiling water.
Stir until dissolves.
Fold in pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.
Thoroughly mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spread this on top of jello mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add horseradish and garlic powder. Spread thinly on slice of ham.
Add thin slice of green onion or pickle or olives with pimento.
Roll up.
Slice thin.
Can make up two days before serving.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together for a tossed salad.

title: tostado casserole
directions: In a skillet brown the beef.
Drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Mix well.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 2 cups corn chips.
Crush the rest of the corn chips and set aside.
Spoon meat mixture over chips in pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with beans and spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and crushed corn chips. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl: flour, sugar and salt.
In saucepan, bring to a boil oleo, shortening, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat well. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes in 9 x 12 pan.
Frost in pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: quick & easy creamy vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle, saute Onion in Butter until tender.
Add Flour, cook and stir until bubbly.
Add Chicken Broth slowly; cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Stir in Milk, Cream, Basil, Salt, Pepper, and Garlic Powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add cooked Vegetables and cooked Orzo Noodles (if desired).
Heat through.
Yields 8 - 10 servings (about 3 quarts).

title: daddy's casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and jalapeno pepper to taste.
Simmer with enchilada sauce and both soups.
Layer in large casserole dish with crushed Doritos on top and bottom.
Put grated cheese on top. Place in oven to melt.

title: quiche
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Add ham and onions; saute for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Combine half and half, eggs, salt and cayenne in mixing bowl and beat thoroughly.
Spread cooked ham and onion mixture evenly over bottom of pie crust. Carefully pour egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon sizzle fajitas and avocado salsa
directions: In shallow pan, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic, chicken base and pepper; mix well.
Reserve 1/3 cup marinade for basting. Store and refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Add meat to remaining mixture.
Cover and marinate 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove meat from marinade.
On hot, oiled grill or griddle, cook meat, green pepper and onion.
Pour reserved marinade over fajita mixture; cook and stir until heated through. Serve each tortilla with 4 ounces of meat mixture and 1/2 cup Avocado Salsa.

title: cranberry jello salad(this is great as a side dish with turkey)
directions: Mix 1 cup boiling water with Jell-O.
Mix second cup of boiling water with cranberry sauce that has been mashed.
Mix Jell-O mixture and cranberry mixture together.
Pour half the mixture in a glass 8 x 11-inch dish.
Jell this portion in the refrigerator.
After it has jelled, take out and spread sour cream over layer.
Slowly spoon and/or pour remainder of Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate to jell.

title: chicken lasagna roll-ups
directions: In a large nonstick pan, cook chicken in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil for 5 to 7 minutes. Add spinach and seasonings. In a saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour to form a paste. Gradually add hot milk, stirring all the time until mixture comes to a boil and thickens. Stir in chicken mixture. Spread a little of the chicken mixture onto each of the lasagna noodles. Roll up tightly and secure with a toothpick. Place in a single layer in a casserole dish. Spoon over tomato sauce. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lasagna noodles are tender.

title: broccoli and noodles
directions: Put all, except cheese and noodles, in a large pan; cook about 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Heat until melted.
Add cooked and drained noodles.
Can use fresh broccoli, chopped.
For a soup, add 3 cups milk.

title: pecan ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar.
Add baking powder and vanilla and beat until mixed.
Add crackers and nuts; pour into a buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool until center sinks, then refrigerate.
Let get real cold.
Put Cool Whip over top to serve.

title: stuffed squid
directions: Remove ink sac and bones from squid.
Wash thoroughly.
Remove head and entrails from body.
Cut feelers from head and chop very fine together with entrails.
Place in bowl.
Add rice, 1/2 cup olive oil, mint leaves, tomato paste, tomatoes, salt and pepper and mix well.
Stuff squids and replace heads to keep filling from coming out.
Arrange in baking dish and pour remaining juice from stuffing over squids.
Add remaining oil and water and bake in hot oven (475°) for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 minutes longer or until rice is tender.
Baste occasionally. Serve very hot.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix and marinate for at least 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: nachos and cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese and add tomatoes; stir with wire whisk.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
Reserve one soup can of broth.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Set aside.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Pat pizza dough into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer with hash browns, meat and cheese. Beat together eggs and milk. Pour over all. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: soup for the gang
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato paste, hamburger, water and seasoning.
Mix well.
Add vegetables; cover and let boil gently for 1 hour.
Simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking to pan.
Serve hot or freeze.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: Ready in 10 minutes!

title: peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place peeled, sliced peaches in buttered 8 inch casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, nutmeg, and margarine in a bowl; then sprinkle mixture over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Wash and prepare tomatoes and apples, cutting out core and any spots.
Quarter or cut in 6ths; grind and drain.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Salt broccoli; boil for 10 minutes in 1 cup water.
Remove broccoli; add it to onions and celery.
Add soup and milk.
Add cheese to this mixture; simmer for 1 minute.
Add rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat.
Heat in separate pan, the next 5 ingredients, to boiling.
Add to meat along with celery and onions.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Serve on buns.

title: hawaiian island style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat.
Add reserved pineapple juice, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover and cook 40 minutes. Add green peppers and pineapple chunks and cook 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and water; gradually add to mixture and cook until thickened.
Serve with cooked parsley rice.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, bring 2 cups milk, uncooked rice and raisins to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and cook over very low heat about 15 minutes or until rice is done.
Remove from heat; stir in butter or oleo until melted.
In a mixing bowl, stir together the eggs, the 2 cups of milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.

title: roasted asparagus with thyme
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place asparagus in a roasting pan or baking pan lined with heavy-duty foil.
Drizzle with oil and toss to coat.
Sprinkle with the thyme, salt and pepper.
Bake uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Serves 12.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Blend dry ingredients; combine with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Select small beets; cook until tender.
Dip into cold water. Peel off skins.
Make the syrup.
Pour over beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack into sterilized Kerr jars and seal.
A little grated horseradish added to pickled beets gives variety.

title: egg pie
directions: Mix together.
Cook until thick.
Pour into prepared pie shell.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Slice apples very thin.
Place in baking dish; top with loaf bread, cut to fit baking dish.

title: angel hair hot dish
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water with onion and the bouillon cubes.
(The broth will be used to cook the pasta, so use enough to cook the angel hair.)
When done, remove chicken and add pasta. Cook until tender.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add almond extract. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth. Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Turn the mixture into the pan.
Spoon the pie filling into the cake, in 16 or so spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and cake tests done.
Filling will sink into cake while baking. To serve, cut into pieces and place bottom side up. Dust with powdered sugar. Serve with whipped cream, if desired. This is great served warm!

title: marinade for beef or chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over meat and refrigerate for 2 hours. Turn meat over and marinate 2 more hours or overnight.
Can be used more than once.

title: garlic cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine baking mix, milk and Cheddar cheese in mixing bowl. Beat with wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Mix butter and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.

title: liver and onions plus
directions: In a large cast iron skillet (which has been sprayed with PAM), put on low heat and add:
tomato juice, bell pepper, sliced onion, celery, garlic powder, pepper.
Raise heat (to high).
Bring liquid ingredients to a strong simmer and add calves liver.
Cover pan and cook for 5 minutes.
Uncover and turn over and poach for another 3 minutes.
Serve liver, with liquid, over rice.
Delicious even to those who don't like liver!
Yield:
4 servings.

title: apple delight cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar and let stand for a little while.
Mix dry ingredients together and combine with apples and sugar; add eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, egg yolks, spices and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add evaporated milk.
Beat just until blended.

title: meat loaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in 8 x 8-inch greased pan and season with garlic powder.
Microwave for 20 to 25 minutes on High or bake at 350°. Also works well with ground turkey or chicken bouillon.

title: shrimp-a-la-hunter(hand-down from bull hunter)
directions: Salt and pepper shrimp.
Shake shrimp into flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Lightly brown shrimp, over low heat, in melted butter.
Cover with water; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in large casserole dish at 350° for about 1 hour.
If desired, sprinkle Italian bread crumbs over the top before baking.

title: spinach souffle salad
directions: Add gelatin to boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and mix well.
Add ice cold water and stir well.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Add spinach, celery, onion and cheese.
Blend well, turn into 9-inch square pan and stir again.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 9.

title: lollipop m&m cookies
directions: You will also need tongue depressors.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk and fig juice.
Add alternately to egg mix. Add vanilla and fold in figs and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: toll house marble squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in the egg.
Blend in the flour, soda and salt.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over the top of the dough. Place in the oven 1 minute at 375°.
Remove from the oven and run a knife through the dough.
Return and bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cut in 2 inch squares.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt; mix well.
Chill; shape into a 4-inch ball and roll in pecans.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 cups.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 6-cup souffle dish, or deep dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Remove all skin and bones from fish in a saucepan.
Combine flour, Butter Buds and milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat; beat in egg substitute, mustard, tarragon and celery.
Add fish.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Gently fold in fish mixture; pour into prepared dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in each graham cracker crust.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: pork chops
directions: Mix together mushroom soup and sour cream.
Place all ingredients in shallow pan.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top. Cover with foil and bake in 300° to 325° oven for 3 hours.

title: taco dip(appetizer)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan melt butter; sprinkle evenly, crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, Eagle Brand milk and pecans in that order.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool at least 2 hours before cutting.

title: hash browns au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Gently mix together potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine corn flakes and remaining margarine.
Spoon onto potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour, until puffed and crust has formed.
Pretty and delicious.

title: lime-scallion-cuke jello mold
directions: Pour hot water over Jell-O.
Dissolve.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Pour in Jell-O and stir.
Beat thoroughly.
Add cucumbers and onions.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Cake:
Combine cake mix and pudding in a large bowl.
Blend in eggs, oil, 4 ounces liqueur Galliano, 1 ounce vodka and 4 ounces orange juice.
Mix batter until smooth and thick.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove and place on rack.
Have glaze ready to spoon on while cake is still warm.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: healthy cheesecake
directions: Blend first five ingredients with electric mixer.
Blend in sour cream and egg whites.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with nonfat cooking spray; sprinkle with crumbs.
Pour in cheese mixture and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool, then refrigerate for 3 hours. Top with berries or cherries.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra into 1/2-inch pieces. Season with salt. Pour a small amount buttermilk over okra, just enough to make flour stick. Roll in flour until coated well. Fry a small amount at a time on medium heat until crisp and brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs (one at a time), water, strawberries.
Flour three 8 inch pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: In medium skillet, fry 1 pound ground beef; drain and add red kidney beans and set aside to cool.
In large salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, green pepper and onion (prepare like a salad). Add the cooled ground beef and bag of Doritos.
Top with entire bottle of Catalina dressing and serve.

title: salt substitute
directions: Combine all together.
Put in spice jar and store in cool dry place.

title: paradise cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour into greased (not floured) 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk.
Spread over cooled cake. Drain crushed pineapple and with fingers spread over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: pickle relish
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients.
Combine and soak overnight in water and salt mixture.
Drain, then add vinegar, brown sugar, mustard and turmeric.
Cook slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is done.
Garnish with green onions.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in bowl. Heat margarine and cake to boiling and pour over flour and sugar. Add milk, soda, eggs and vanilla. Add marshmallows last. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes in a rectangular pan. Batter is very thin.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening and salt into crumbs; keep 1 1/3 cups out for top of cake.
Add liquid and baking soda.
Mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh lemon sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into ice trays or square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze about 4 hours.
Makes 1 quart.

title: play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and aluminum.
Boil water and oil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Stir rapidly until all is moistened.
Turn out onto a plate and cover with a towel until cool enough to handle.
Stir in airtight container.
Keeps longer in the refrigerator.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain each can of beans and combine thoroughly in large bowl. To beans, add green pepper and onion.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind apricots and orange together in food chopper, using fine grind.
Cook apricots and orange with sugar in top of double boiler until all sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add coconut. Cool on tray.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar. Store several days in closed container.
Roll again in powdered sugar.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates, butter and sugar.
Cool.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to the date mixture.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Pour into a lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes or slightly longer, then reduce heat to 300°.
Continue baking for 1 hour.

title: broccoli, mushroom, water chestnut stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, saute garlic in sesame oil for 1 minute. Add mushrooms. Cook until moisture is out.
Add broccoli and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry for about 3 minutes. Add noodles, soy sauce and green onion.
Toss together well. Steam for 2 more minutes, then serve.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease pans (2 loaves) or 3 smaller size.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together (about 2 minutes).
Bake for 1 hour or little less if in 3 pans.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Mix in sugars, egg, peanut butter, margarine and shortening until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough by teaspoonfuls into 2 1/2-inch fingers on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, about 8 minutes; cool.
Dip one end of each cookie into Cocoa Glaze. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together thoroughly.
Beat in one egg at a time until all 4 are added.
Stir in part of sifted flour and baking powder; mix thoroughly.
Then alternately add milk and flour.
Add vanilla and flavoring.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Place oven rack in lowest position.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) or 1 loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix sugar and butter in a large bowl.
Stir in eggs until well blended.
Add bananas, buttermilk and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts. Stir in nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 8-inch loaves about 1 hour, 9-inch loaf about 1 1/4 hours or when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: "el paso" border city chile con queso
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent.
Add cheese and milk.
Let cheese melt.
Be sure to stir as it will burn if not careful.
Add Ro-Tel and chiles.
Cook slow 3 to 4 hours.
If too thin, grate and add more cheese.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas to soften; roll in chicken, cheese, peppers and Tabasco sauce and fasten.
When finished, pour in soup and sour cream. Top with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute large can (8 ounce) mushrooms in 1/4 pound butter.
Add 5 cups of diced chicken (1 whole).
Heat 2 cans cream of mushroom soup and 1 pint of sour cream together.
Add a little cooking sherry and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in 1 package spaghetti, cooked.
(Cut spaghetti in 3 or 4 pieces before boiling in salted water.)
Mix all well with chicken and mushrooms.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian noodle bake
directions: Combine ingredients, then mix with 1 package of egg noodles.

title: christmas relish
directions: Chop all peppers and onions and pour boiling water over them and let set 5 minutes.
Drain.
Chop the celery and mix all together and bring to a boil.
Combine the sugar, vinegar and salt and pour on and seal.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips; cream all together.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake pie crust for 5 minutes. Cool. Combine sugar, flour, butter, salt and egg yolks; beat until smooth; add lemon juice and zest. beat at low, then add milk. Beat eggs whites until stiff. Fold them into lemon mixture. Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 minutes until center is set.

title: cream cheese salsa dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix cream cheese and salsa with an electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Serve with assorted cut-up vegetables or low-fat chips.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs, then add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour scalded milk; stir and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie before putting it into the oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, when knife is poked into pie and comes out clean.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Drain vegetables and mushrooms.
Mix well with other ingredients.
Pour into large baking container.

title: spinach salad ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add vinegar and mayonnaise.
When cool, beat.
Cook and cool spinach, drain well.
Add celery, onions, cheese and spinach to gelatin.
Put into a 6-cup mold (or 9 x 12-inch doubled recipe).
Chill until firm.

title: mexicali party dip
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine tomatoes, chilies, cheese and hot pepper sauce.
Microwave at Medium for 7 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: rotel cheese and meat dip
directions: Cook meat.
Brown and drain off grease.
Dice bell peppers and onions; saute until tender.
Combine with meat.
Cut up Ro-Tel tomatoes; add juice.
Combine all into soup.
Put into crock-pot and serve.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Roll each biscuit between hands to form 9-inch ropes.
Pinch ends together to form circles.
Dip biscuit circles in melted butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Twist biscuits to form figure 8's.
Place biscuits on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage and grits casserole
directions: Fry sausage and drain.
Cook grits in boiling, salted water. Stir frequently for 5 minutes.
Add oleo and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, eggs and sausage.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: herbed crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Stir every 15 minutes for 2 hours.
Store in airtight container.
Delicious party snack.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil together syrup, water and sugar until mixture spins a light thread or to the crackling stage on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts begin to pop.
Remove from heat and add salt and soda.
Stir until a golden brown and pour onto a well buttered cookie sheet.
If a darker brown is desired, return to heat a few seconds before pouring on cookie sheet.

title: holiday pumpkin pie
directions: Fit pastry loosely into pie pan. Fold edge to form standing rim; flute. Prick crust with fork. Combine 1/3 cup pecans,

1/3 cup brown sugar and soft butter; press firmly into bottom of pie shell. Combine pumpkin, 1 cup brown sugar, evaporated milk, eggs, salt, spices, orange juice and boiling water in a large mixing bowl until well blended (I use my mixer). Pour mix into pie shell and bake in preheated oven at 450° for 45 to 55 minutes. To keep crust from burning, cover edge with foil after 20 minutes baking time. Chill. Top with whipped cream or whipped topping and serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Fold ham around cheese slices; tuck in each pocket of chicken breast.
Melt butter.
Mix bread crumbs, salt and paprika.
Roll stuffed chicken in melted butter, then in crumbs to coat well. Place in a single layer in buttered baking dish.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Baste if you wish. Can be prepared and frozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream and strawberry cream cheese until well blended.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Goes well with grapes, apple wedges and graham cracker sticks.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Break angel food cakes into bite size pieces.
Mix together egg yolks, butter, powdered sugar and 5 Butterfinger candy bars.
Pour mixture over angel food cake pieces.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining candy bar on top of pie.
Keep refrigerated.
It is better if it is chilled overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Add soup, catsup and mustard.
Cook together.

title: oatmeal butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan*.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla lightly.
Add grated zucchini.
Mix in separate bowl the dry ingredients, then add to the egg-zucchini mixture.
Then add oats and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Crumble bacon.
Cook chopped onions in drippings until tender.
Add with bacon to brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa, milk and sugar for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and let dry.

title: supper casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in frying pan.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, until rice is done.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will need 24 wooden sticks with rounded ends.

title: granola
directions: Mix oatmeal, wheat germ, flaked coconut and sesame seed and set aside.	Mix oil, honey, brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour over oatmeal
mixture
and
mix thoroughly.
Spread evenly in jelly roll pan
Toast at 250° for 1 hour, stirring
every
15 minutes.
Cool, stirring often to keep it from
forming
hard
lumps.
Toss
with 1 cup chopped walnuts or slivered
almonds
and
cup
raisins.
Store in tightly covered container.	Makes about 8 cups.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and beat well the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix on top.
Melt 1 1/2 cubes margarine; pour over top.
Add the desired amount of chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until crisp and brown. Very good!

title: creamed corn
directions: Remove shucks and silk from corn. Wash thoroughly and cut corn off cobs. Place in saucepan with water. Season to suit your taste. (May use 2 tablespoons bacon grease.) Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes on low heat. Add margarine. Combine flour and cold milk until smooth; stir in with corn. Cook another 5 or 10 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries with 1 cup water in sauce pan. Cook until all berries pop.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup water, jello. When cool add celery and pecans.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: apple sauce cake
directions: Beat eggs, margarine, apple sauce, sugar and butter. Add flour and spices. Mix well and add raisins, orange slices and pecans. Bake in a well greased and floured bundt pan at 300 degrees for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: holly berry cookies
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows over low heat; stir until smooth. Add coloring and vanilla.
Stir well; add cornflakes.
Drop spoonfuls on buttered sheet of wax paper.
Add 3 red hots in center.

title: barbecue chicken pizza
directions: Prepare pizza dough like package directions, then spread barbecue sauce over dough.
Sprinkle chicken over sauce.
Arrange green pepper slices over chicken, then top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until dough is brown.

title: orange-cinnamon coffee
directions: Place coffee and orange peel in food processor.
While running, add vanilla.
Scrape sides.
Process for 10 seconds longer.
Mix in a bowl; stir in cinnamon sticks.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Brew in coffee filter as you normally would use automatic drip coffeemaker.
Great gift idea!

title: peanut butter surprise
directions: Mix peanut butter and brown sugar together until smooth.
Stir in M&M's.

title: bush's best santa fe pinto beans
directions: In a large skillet, saute green pepper, onion and garlic in oil for 3 minutes.
Stir in broth and cumin.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add black beans, pinto beans, tomatoes, corn and vinegar.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.
Delicious with grilled chicken.

title: farmer's market omelette(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a large (10 or 12-inch) pan, fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Add pepper and onion to bacon drippings; saute until crisp-tender.
Add potatoes and stir gently to coat.

title: crock-pot barbecue pork
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Pour over mixture of vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook for 8 to 10 hours.
Make sauce with the rest of the ingredients.
Pull meat apart and add sauce.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients; put in baking dish.
Put 1/4 cup crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken breasts, boned side up, in a large Baggie (Ziploc, Glad).
Pound lightly with mallet to make 1/4-inch thick cutlets, working from center out. Sprinkle lightly with salt. Place cheese slice on chicken cutlet.
Cover with ham. Roll up and tuck in sides.
Press to seal well.
Use toothpicks to hold together, if needed. Roll in bread crumbs.
Heat oil in heavy skillet; brown chicken.
Remove to an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Combine 1/2 cup water, Sauterne, bouillon and mushrooms in the same skillet.
Heat, stirring to remove crusty bits from skillet.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tender. Serves 6.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Pour evaporated milk into large bowl. Put bowl and beaters in freezer until ice crystals form around edges of evaporated milk. Whip until stiff peaks form. Fold in chocolate syrup, vanilla, sugar and whipping cream.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry tea muffins
directions: Beat the 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately with butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Fold in blueberries (drained).
Bake in muffin tins or cupcake papers at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir together; do not use mixer.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar mixed with 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed onion leaves
directions: Place the whole, unpeeled onions in a pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, then turn down to a simmer.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove, drain and cool the onions so that you can handle them.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix together the sugar, water, lemon juice and cinnamon; stir well with fork.
Add peeled and sliced apples.
In a separate bowl, add flour, margarine and salt; mix together well (should be crumbly).
Crumble flour mixture over apples; sprinkle a little cinnamon and sugar on the top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and pour into greased loaf pan.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hamburger dumpling casserole
directions: Mix the ground beef, egg, sour cream, onion soup mix and diced bread and shape into small meatballs.
Roll the meatballs in the flour and paprika.
Mix and brown in butter.
Mix the mushrooms, liquid, cream of chicken soup and water and pour over meatballs and simmer while making dumplings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and squash in butter until tender.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder; stir.
In saucepan heat cream of chicken soup and mix all ingredients together. Pour mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and stir in sour cream.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until very light and creamy.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flours, baking soda and salt.

title: beef chowder
directions: Brown ground meat; drain and continue to simmer until meat has cooked.
Add soups and water.
You may add chopped green pepper, if desired (adds color).
Simmer until completely warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hidden pear salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pear liquid to a boil.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved; cool until syrupy.
Puree pears in blender.
Mix cream cheese and lemon juice until fluffy and smooth; add pears. Prepare whipped topping and add pear mixture.
Fold in cooled gelatin.
Pour in oiled 4 1/2 cup mold; chill overnight.
Unmold salad on a lettuce-lined platter.

title: isalata alassio
directions: On a platter, arrange alternating slices of tomato and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with basil and dribble oil and vinegar. Salt and pepper to taste.
Great with barbecue or any hot weather meal.
Yields 6 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix well; chill.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: sausage pie
directions: Place sausages on a rack in baking pan, bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into 1-inch pieces; set aside.
In a skillet, saute peppers in oil for 3 minutes.

Place in a 3-quart casserole; add the sausages and the rice, tomatoes, corn, Cheddar cheese, Worcestershire, salt, parsley and basil. Combine bread crumbs and butter, sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix or layer ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cajun-style buffalo wings
directions: Combine chicken wings, sauces and all spices in large saucepan. Cover and heat on low several hours until chicken is cooked through.

title: fresh coconut pie
directions: Mix everything together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: becky's muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, egg and milk.
Mix together.
Last, add berries.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix in crab. Season to taste with hot pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Serve with endive spears, bell pepper strips, celery, assorted crackers and breadsticks.

title: acadian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with 1 1/4 teaspoons of the salt and pepper.
In large heavy skillet, cook breasts in melted butter over medium-high heat until golden brown on both sides. Remove.
Place in large shallow baking pan.
In saucepan, dissolve bouillon cubes
in the boiling water.
Pour half over chicken. Sprinkle with lemon juice and dried onion flakes.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk. Add shortening and corn.
Combine flour and corn mixture.
Stir only until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a sizzling hot skillet.
Fry until golden brown on each side.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pickled green beans
directions: Clean 4 pint jars and put fresh washed raw green beans in each jar. Add 1 piece dill and 1 garlic clove. Bring to a boil the vinegar, water and salt. Pour hot liquid over beans 1/4-inch from top of jar. Can in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: crab fettuccine
directions: Add oil to boiling water; cook pasta and drain.
Saute garlic in oil until tender.
Add basil, cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add crab meat and heat.
Add wine; cook 15 minutes.
Add soy sauce and butter.
Serve over pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Garnish with lemon and parsley.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine onion, sour cream, soup, cheese, butter and seasonings in a bowl.
Mix well. Pour over the potatoes; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage.
Drain.
Save water.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add bread crumbs.
Stir and set aside.

title: rabbit sauce piquante
directions: If using wild rabbit, plunge into deep pot of boiling water and boil for 10 minutes.
This is necessary in order to remove the wild taste.
Fry each piece of rabbit until golden brown in deep fat.
Remove rabbit and set aside.
Retain 6 to 8 tablespoons fat.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: Blanch peas for 3 minutes in boiling salt water.
Transfer rice to a mixing bowl and pour 1 1/2 cups Vinaigrette into rice.
Toss thoroughly.
Cool to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients and toss thoroughly.
Taste, correct seasoning, and add additional Vinaigrette if you like.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 4 hours.
Return to room temperature before serving.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in small amount of oil until the vegetables are limp.
Open and drain 2 cans of salmon. Put in mixing bowl and take off as much skin and center bones as you can.
Mash salmon and add eggs.
Add vegetable mixture; blend well.
Add cracker crumbs.
Add salt, pepper, onion powder and garlic powder to taste.
Add extra egg.
Spray a 9 x 14-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Put mixture in.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: mocha chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter and add 1 cup of powdered sugar and cocoa slowly. Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 1 cup of powdered sugar to it gradually.
Add coffee to the butter mixture to help incorporate balance of powdered sugar.
Then add both mixtures together and beat until fluffy and of spreading consistency.
Will frost 1 double layer cake.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix cheese, soup and milk. Pour half in a 9 x 12 pan. Separate rolls and place cut up chicken in and roll tucking edges in. Place in mixture. Then spoon the other half of sauce over rolls. Bake at 30 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes or slightly browned.

title: broccoli chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, cut up chicken into cubes and saute in butter until lightly brown.
Set aside.
In a bowl, mix 2 cans soup, 1 can broth and 1/2 cup mayo.
Add your chicken and mix.
Prepare your stuffing according to directions on box; set aside.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add rice and cook until brown.
Add peppers and onion and saute.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir well.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together, reserving 1 cup of cheese for topping.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into greased, large casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, covered.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off ends of zucchini and cut them in half, lengthwise.
Cook zucchini in 1-inch deep salted boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes, until crisp, yet tender.
Drain.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Chop enough pulp to make about 3/4 cup.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine with remaining ingredients, including pulp.
Spoon evenly into zucchini shells. Place shells into a greased 9 X 13-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the last 5 ingredients.
Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Precook peppers in salted water for 3 minutes.

title: italian shells casserole
directions: Cook shells (al dente).
Rinse, drain and set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add salt and pepper and stir in marinara sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
In a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer 1/2 the shells, 1/2 the sauce, 1/2 the sour cream and 1/2 of each bag of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook together for 10 minutes, the water, bouillon, celery, onion and potatoes, then add the frozen vegetables.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more, then add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Do not boil.
Makes 4-quarts and freezes well.

title: kraut supreme
directions: Mix kraut, sugar and tomatoes.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Add a little melted bacon grease and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover while baking.

title: brown beef stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Add water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion, bay leaves and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours; stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: hot lobster dip
directions: Whip mayonnaise together with cream cheese and garlic powder. Mix well.
Fold lobster meat into mayo mixture; spread thinly into a buttered 9 x 10-inch glass or casserole dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or toast rounds.

title: vinegar pie crust(impossible to ruin!)
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add sugar and salt.
Mix together in a cup the vinegar, egg and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Chill 15 minutes.
Makes 2 pies and 1 shell.
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken with all but cheese.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes before serving.
Heat oven to 375°.
Put mixture in casserole. Top with cheese. Bake about 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Put in buttered muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Dip top of muffins in melted butter and sugar.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Slice onion on top of ribs in roast pan.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Baste ribs.
Roast for 2 hours at 350°.
Baste frequently.

title: microwave egg and cheese casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into large glass bowl, microwave, covered with plastic wrap, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, turning bowl once.
Drain.
Add milk, eggs, dry mustard, salt, cheese and bread; mix well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (uncovered).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole dish.
