Crush 1 package Ritz crackers over the top and cut up 1 stick of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: lynn's pork barbecue
directions: Cook 4 hours at 350° or until meat can be pulled apart.
Stir and remove excess fat after pulling apart.

title: moravian christmas loaf
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water.
Add the 3 cups flour and salt gradually to the 2 cups cooled milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in the yeast.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Add 1 cup scalded milk to the butter and sugar; stir until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm; stir into the yeast mixture.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Stir in a mixture of the fruits.
Knead the dough on a floured surface until smooth and satiny, adding flour as needed.
Place in a greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 2 hours.
Punch down dough and divide into 4 portions.
Shape into loaves and place in 4 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans. Brush tops of loaves with melted shortening; sprinkle with almonds. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rigatoni vodka
directions: Place bacon and onion in pan and cook.
When bacon begins to brown, remove.
Add smoked salmon and vodka.
(Take the pan away from the flame when adding vodka.)
Allow to simmer several minutes, then add marinara sauce, Parmesan cheese, heavy cream and egg yolks.
Simmer for several minutes, then toss in rigatoni. Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: spiced fruits
directions: Drain fruit syrup into saucepan; add sugar, vinegar, and spices and boil 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over fruit and cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Drain if desired before serving.

title: southwestern beef hash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large skillet over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink.
Pour off drippings. Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Increase heat to medium-high and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salsa. Continue cooking 8 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are lightly browned, stirring occasionally.

title: cake that don't last
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel, then scrape cukes lengthwise with a fork to remove acid. Slice thinly.
Make a layer of cukes in a medium to large bowl. Sprinkle very lightly with salt.
Continue layers of cukes and salt.
Press for 4 hours.
(I use a small plate and an empty bottle filled with water.)
Drain.
Cover with vinegar; press again for 2 hours.
Drain in strainer for 1/2 hour.
Mix with cream and a dash or two of pepper.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in juice, garlic and seasonings 15 minutes. Cook chicken in oil 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken looses pink color.
Add peppers and onions.
Continue cooking 3 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Spoon onto tortillas.
Top with salsa and cheese.
Yields 4 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika together.
Cut meat into portions; pound flour mixture into steak and brown in oleo.
Saute onion.
Mix onion, water and sour cream until well blended.
Pour over meat; cover and cook over medium heat 35 to 45 minutes. Uncover and cook until sauce thickens (10 to 15 minutes).
Serves 8.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in bottom of heavy roaster.
Cover with layer of sliced onion.
Mix rest of ingredients to make barbecue sauce. Pour over top.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 325° until meat is tender, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours according to thickness of spareribs.
Remove to platter and serve while hot.

title: cheese macaroni
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add flour and cook until smooth.
Add milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add diced cheese when sauce begins to thicken.
Boil water for noodles; add salt.
After noodles are cooked, remove and drain; put in buttered dish.
Add melted cheese sauce to macaroni and sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg salad dijon
directions: In small bowl, mix eggs, mayonnaise, mustard and relish until well blended.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.

title: date cake
directions: Put chopped dates in boiler with 1 cup boiling water and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour and salt alternately in thirds with water, soda and dates.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350°
in a 9-inch square pan until done.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water. Add orange juice. Add undrained crushed pineapple and 2 cups drained mandarin oranges. Pour into 13 x 9 dish. After it is set, mix vanilla pudding, 1 cup milk and Cool Whip. Top with this mixture.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Beat eggs and add sugar and flour to them. Bake in uncooked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash as usual.
Saute onion and green pepper in oleo. Mix with cooked, drained squash.
Beat egg.
Mix with creamed corn.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole. Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat several minutes.
Add flour and milk; begin with flour and end with flour.
Beat several minutes.
Add flavoring.
Pour cake in cake pans; will make 4 layers.

title: black bean soup
directions: Clean beans, soak overnight in water to cover (drain).
Make chicken stock by dissolving bouillon cubes in 1 1/2 gallons hot water, in a 5 gallon pot.
Add drained beans and ham shank.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to medium and cook until beans are tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chutney and cheese spread
directions: Take a fresh pineapple and slice in half, taking pineapple out and using shell as the dish.
Blend cream cheese, mustard, chutney and curry powder in food processor with an off-on motion until well blended.
Put into pineapple shell and top with toasted almonds.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving with crackers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil, stirring until ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped pecans and bananas. Put into greased and floured cake pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Cool when done.

title: orange-sliced cookies
directions: Mix well and roll in a large or 4 small rolls.
Chill until firm and slice.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine raisins and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie bars
directions: With mixer, beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Stir in flour and walnuts until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture on bottom of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Meanwhile, blend pumpkin, condensed milk, molasses, eggs, pumpkin pie spice, and vanilla; pour over pastry crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Bake 30 to 35 minutes more or until set.
Cool in pan or wire rack. Drizzle with powdered sugar glaze if desired.
Cut into 3 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bar.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: grapefruit-avocado salad
directions: Bring to boil sugar, 1 cup water and grapefruit juice.
Add 2 envelopes gelatin that has been dissolved in 9 tablespoons water. Set aside.
Arrange avocado slices in bottom of pan.
(I grease pan first with oil.)
Pour 1/2 of gelatin mixture over avocado slices. After gelatin is firm, spread over all, the cream cheese that has been blended with mayonnaise.
Drain grapefruit perfectly and arrange sections over cheese.
Pour remaining gelatin over grapefruit.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares. Using spatula, turn out on lettuce leaf.
This is very good!

title: quick chicken cobbler
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine soups, vegetables and chicken broth.
Mix well.
Add spices and mix until thoroughly blended. Pour mixture into a 10-inch Kitchen Fry shallow pan.
Place biscuits on top of chicken mixture.
Cover.
Place on medium heat.
Turn heat to low when lid is hot to touch.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peppermint chocolate cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream oleo at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add sugar 1 cup at a time.
mix well.
Beat eggs and add 1 at a time.
Mix for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla, butter, chocolate and peppermint extract.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add milk and sour cream.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into waxed paper lined tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 75 to 90 minutes. Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: frosty rainbow pie(lime, pink lemonade, lemonade, pineapple or orange)
directions: Bake pie shell as directed and cool.
Beat 3 egg whites at room temperature until soft peaks form.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar gradually until stiff.
Beat in 3 egg yolks at low speed.
Beat in thawed Cool Whip topping until blended.
Beat in 1/3 cup of one of the following choices of frozen juice, thawed and undiluted, and add appropriate food coloring:
lime Juice (green food coloring), pink lemonade (tiny bit of red food coloring), lemonade or pineapple juice (yellow food coloring), orange juice (red + yellow food coloring).
Mound into pie shell.
Freeze several hours until firm.
Serve frozen and refreeze unused portion.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, peanut butter, butter and vanilla together.
Shape into balls; dip into melted paraffin and semi-sweet chocolate chips.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together butter and sugar; add the next 3 ingredients. Add applesauce. Dissolve soda in warm water, then add to mixture. Sift flour and salt together, then mix with mixture. Bake 45 minutes. Allow cooling before removing from pan.

title: puerto rican beef stew
directions: In a large heavy kettle or pot, heat vegetable oil.
Add chunks of beef and stir constantly over moderate-high heat until brown.

title: my grandmother's stewed shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour gradually; cook to a light brown.
Add onions; saute until golden.
Add shrimp; mix well.
Let cool slightly.
Add tomatoes, water, green pepper and seasoning.
Cook, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Combine and mix until well blended.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in 8 1/2 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs; mash.
Put in butterscotch chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour milk over ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, melted butter and pecans.
Press evenly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: city chicken
directions: Put meat on sticks.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Dip in evaporated milk and cracker crumbs.
Brown in frypan.
Put in baking pan.
Add salt and pepper.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cold leftovers are very good.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until piping hot.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; add shells and chill.
Can add cheese, pepperoni and vegetables.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise, remove yolks and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except last 2 and mix until smooth.
Fill egg whites with the mixture and chill.
Dust with paprika and garnish with parsley.
Makes 12, about 42 calories each.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: In a bowl, mix bread crumbs with salt and pepper; set aside. Lightly pound each chicken breast and dip in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Brown quickly in hot oil and remove to casserole. Remove excess oil.
Add tomato sauce and spices to skillet.
Heat to boiling, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Add butter and pour this over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese, cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese and bake 10 minutes longer, uncovered.
Serves 4 generously.

title: four layer lemon torte
directions: Mix together and put into 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: easy southern cookies
directions: Beat egg white and salt until stiff.
Stir in brown sugar and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Combine ingredients in punch bowl and add approximately 1/2 gallon of rainbow sherbet before serving.

title: irish potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda and add alternately with milk to potato mixture, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream or whipped topping on each piece.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients on medium until Crisco has melted.
The mixture needs to be warm but not hot.
Remove from heat and mix in 2 cups of flour, yeast and eggs (already beaten). Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise 1 hour and punch down.
Make out rolls; let rise 30 minutes and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 24 rolls, depending on size.

title: crisco frosting
directions: In a large mixing bowl, on medium speed, mix Crisco until fluffy and creamy.
Add salt, water and flavoring and mix.
Add 1/2 box of sugar at a time.
After adding all of one box of sugar, lower mixer speed to low to mix remaining sugar in well.
Beat until smooth.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add oats and mix.
Add to butter mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Press flat with fingers.
Press crisscross on top with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: low-fat finger lickin' good chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients except chicken in a glass baking dish.
Coat chicken in apricot mixture and lay flat in dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over. Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake another 30 minutes until done.
Serve with steamed carrots.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories 337; cholesterol 144 mg., fat 6 grams; sodium 114 mg.

title: my pea picking cake
directions: Mix cake mix and oranges together and bake as box indicates. Bake in 2 small layer pans.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugar, beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well.
Add flour and soda to mixture, then add the buttermilk and vanilla.
Add coconut.
Fold in the egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Grease and flour 3 cake (layer) pans.

title: taverns
directions: Bring the water to a boil in a large pan.
Crumble beef and add it to the water along with the rest of the ingredients.
Bring the mixture to a boil for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring to mix well, and break up any lumps of meat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
To serve, spoon mixture on hamburger buns that have been wrapped in foil and warmed in the oven.
Every kid from 5 to 50 will love 'em!

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add salt and cornmeal gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbles.
Remove from heat and serve immediately.

title: fay massie's hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add onion.
Add egg and milk, stirring lightly.
Drop a teaspoon of batter for each hush puppy into hot deep fat (360°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Add cut up chicken.
I use about 4 to 5 chicken breasts.

title: cheese balls
directions: Cut up Velveeta and cream cheese; let stand until soft.
Grate in Cheddar.
Season with garlic salt, onion salt and 2 teaspoons Lea & Perrins Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well with hands and form into balls or logs and roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Wrap again in foil.
Store in refrigerator; will keep for weeks.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, separate into bite-size pieces.
Add onions and celery; simmer until tender.
Combine ground beef mixture with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Rice can be served with dish if desired.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Put cleaned vegetables and bacon in a large bowl.
Mix sugar, water and flour; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and boil until it is thick and clear.
Cool and then add mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix with electric mixer and keep in refrigerator.
Mix what you need with vegetables just before serving.

title: microwave chili dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs lengthwise.
Spoon chili onto hot dogs (generously).
Add onions and heat on High in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Sprinkle generous amount of cheese on top.
Put back into microwave for 30 seconds.
Place in buns.

title: walnut sauce(intxaur salsa; walnut pudding)
directions: The bread crumbs are optional; however, if not used, double the amount of walnuts.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and oleo; add rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt butter and chocolate; cool a little.
Blend in sugar and eggs and beat.
Add in dry ingredients and nuts.
Chill.
Shape into walnut size balls and roll in some confectioners sugar.
Bake on greased sheet for 18 to 20 minutes at 300° or for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy. Stir in potatoes and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Combine syrup, milk, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 35 minutes in pie pan.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Brown and drain sausage. Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into medium size balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate pie(like a frozen chocolate pie)
directions: Whip cream until stiff and fold into the chocolate frosting. Spoon mixture into crust.
Then mix 1 pint heavy whipping cream sweetened with a little sugar and vanilla.
Put over top of pie. Freeze.
This pie is a lot better than the frozen pie you buy at the store.

title: chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes or so until tender.
Put in hot jars.
Cook hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put cracker crumbs and butter on top.
Bake until steaming hot!

title: butter tarts
directions: Prepare Crisco pastry recipe for double crusted pie, as directed on package.
Cut into 4-inch rounds.
Fit into medium sized muffin cups.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix in saucepan the blueberries, sugar, flour and water.
Bring to slow boil and cook until mixture is thickened.
Cool.
Mix together margarine, brown sugar, flour and pecans and press flat in square or oblong pan.
Bake at 425° until slightly brown (about 8 minutes).
Let cool.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Wash the kidney beans.
Cut the onion up in small pieces. Slice the hard-boiled eggs.
Save 1 slice of egg for top of dish. Add mayonnaise and sprinkle Salad Supreme in.
Mix it and lay 1 slice egg on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top of egg.

title: "my sole"
directions: Heat soup.
Lay out fish in shallow, greased baking dish.
Bake fish for 20 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 300° and pour soup over fish and continue baking for another 15 minutes.
(Oh, sole easy!)

title: asparagus appetizers
directions: Cook asparagus as directed.
Make a dressing by mixing wine, oil and herbs.
Marinate cooked asparagus in the dressing, in the refrigerator, for at least 1 hour.
Roll each asparagus spear in a slice of ham.
Arrange on a serving plate to serve cold, or heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes and serve warm.
Makes 40 servings.

title: margarita's salsa(dip)
directions: Place tomatoes, garlic and jalapeno peppers in blender and blend on chop until all ingredients are chopped.
Remove and place in bowl.
Manually chop green peppers into small pieces and add to tomatoes.
Add basil, parsley, salt and garlic powder and mix all together.

title: boiled custard(cooking time:  20 minutes.  yield:  5 to 6 cups)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, put 1 cup of applesauce; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon, then crumble bread over top of that.
Use another cup of applesauce; repeat sugar, spice and bread.
Dot top with plenty of butter; bake in 375° oven and brown for about 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 4 loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball. Refrigerate.

title: "easy" cheese cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
You will also need a spring-form pan.

title: brownies
directions: Put oleo, water and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour over flour, sugar and salt mixture.
Add eggs, milk, soda, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry iced tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Remove bags, squeezing out liquid.
Add sugar, lemon juice and cranberry juice cocktail, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Just before serving, stir in club soda.
Pour over ice cubes in tall glasses.

title: chicken in the duck sauce
directions: Mix Russian dressing, preserves and soup mix.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in covered dish.

title: reception punch
directions: Boil sugar with 2 quarts water about 5 minutes.
Have mint steeped and add fruit juices, tea and remaining water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Add frozen strawberries just before serving (optional).
Serves 100.

title: aunt elaine's cream cheese kiefles
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add flour and salt and blend well.
Form into 3 balls; chill several hours.
Roll thin using lots of powdered sugar (not flour) over rolling surface.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Fill.
Do not overfill; filling will bake out.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate syrup pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well and add all ingredients.
Mix for 10 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Start in a cold oven.
Do not open oven door for 1 hour.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: dip that tastes like panchos
directions: Cube cheese (drop in blender).
Add all
other ingredients. Blend until liquified.
If
cheese
is cold, add 1 to 3 tablespoons hot water.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the apples and pineapple juice.
Slice apples.
Put in bowl with pineapple juice to keep apples from turning brown.
Serve with toothpicks for dipping or bowls for apples with sauce on the side.

title: peggy's crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Put cooked macaroni in crock pot. Pour melted oleo over macaroni.
Add shredded cheese, reserving enough for top.
Toss well to mix.
Stir together soup, eggs, and milk.
Mix with macaroni.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cook in crock pot on low for three hours. Makes 20 servings.

title: milk gravy with sausage
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Leave the sausage and natural juices inside skillet.
Keep mixture on medium heat.
Mix thoroughly flour.
More flour may be necessary to properly absorb juices.
Pour in milk, stirring slowly.
Continue to stir until gravy thickens to desired consistency.
Remove from heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Smooth with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Do not overbake.
Cool 15 minutes and invert on plate. Pour hot frosting on immediately.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Blend together and spread onto greased cookie sheet.
Cover with plastic wrap.
bake 2 hours at 200 degrees.
Prop open oven door a small bit while baking.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Pour off fat. Add other ingredients (except cheese and chips). Cover and reduce heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes. Top with cheese. Cover and heat until melted. Serve with corn chips.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Process oil, vinegar, basil, green onions, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper in blender until smooth.
Put pasta, bell pepper strips, tomato wedges and olives in large bowl.
Pour in dressing; toss to mix.
Roll cheese cubes in remaining 2 tablespoons basil to coat.
Add to salad; sprinkle with oregano.
Toss lightly.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 4 main dish servings.

title: baby teething biscuits
directions: Break eggs into a bowl and stir until creamy.
Add sugar and continue to stir.
Gradually add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out between 2 sheets of lightly floured wax paper to about 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut in round shapes.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let stand overnight (10 to 12 hours).
Bake at 325° until browned and hard.
Makes 12 almost crumb-free biscuits.

title: chicken cutlets(italian)
directions: Pound chicken to approximately 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine the egg, milk and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese in one bowl.
In another bowl, mix the bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons of the cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip each cutlet first into the egg wash and then into the bread crumb mixture.
Press the cutlets gently so that the crumbs will adhere to the meat on both sides.

title: peanut butter cookies(for seven dozen cookies)
directions: Melt butter.
Beat together with the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
In a separate bowl combine the flour, bran and baking soda.
Stir mixture into butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Let sugar and milk boil over medium heat until firm ball in cold water forms.
Take off heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir, with bottom of pan sitting in cold water, until it starts to thicken.
Add walnuts, if desired.
Pour in square dish that is buttered on the bottom.
Refrigerate.
Excellent!

title: lemon-pecan mold
directions: Prepare Jell-O with boiling water and salt.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Stir and place in mold.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put all ingredients (except peaches) in pan.
Cook on medium heat; stir until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put peaches on top of batter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar; top with some nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes. Pretty good made with blackberries, also!

title: toad in a hole
directions: Brown sausage in butter.
Arrange both in baking dish.
Sift together flour and salt.
Whisk egg and milk.
Combine together; pour over sausage.
Bake at 300° until brown.
Serve immediately with gravy.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix with mixer and chill.

title: ranch-style frijoles
directions: In casserole, combine onion, chili pepper and oil; stir. Microwave on High 1 minute.
Add tomatoes with liquid, beans, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Stir.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Serve with 3 tortilla wedges.
Serves 2.
Contains 194 calories, 4 gm fat and 705 mg sodium.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Place butter in deep dish.
Heat in a 375° oven.
Heat fruit just to boiling point.
Mix flour and sugar. Add milk and stir until butter is smooth.
Pour batter onto hot butter.
Add heated fruit. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy pickles
directions: Drain the pickles; cut in quarters.
Replace in jar.
Bring to a boil the 4 ingredients listed.
Boil a minute or two, then pour over pickles.
Seal; let stand for 6 weeks.
Sooo good!
And you made them in about 20 minutes.

title: butter pecan salad
directions: Mix pudding, then add rest of ingredients.

title: barbecue hamburger sloppy joes
directions: Brown and
drain ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Steam rice, milk and salt in a double boiler, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
Add sugar, butter and raisins.
Steam 1/2 hour longer.
Remove from heat and fold in eggs and vanilla. Cool.

title: easy appetizers
directions: Wrap each water chestnut in 1/2 strip of bacon.
Fasten with a toothpick.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite sized pieces.
Combine broccoli, bacon, raisins and onions.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Pour dressing over broccoli and toss.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: english muffin bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Add warm milk and water.
Beat on low speed for 30 seconds and on high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour.
Dough will be stiff.
Do not knead.
Grease 2 loaf pans; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon batter into pans.
Sprinkle cornmeal on top.
Cover; let rise until double, about 45 minutes. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately; cool on rack.
Slice and toast.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix altogether, except cornflakes and butter.
Place in large casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cornflakes and butter.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices and press over bottom and sides of 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Cool completely.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients all together in a large kettle overnight in a cool spot.
Next day, add remaining ingredients. Mix with a large wooden spoon, then mix all together.
Put Crisco and flour into bread pans.
Makes 3 large loaves.
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours.
If using smaller pans, bake for a lot less time.
Check with a toothpick for doneness.

title: chicken barley soup
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Cool broth and skim off fat.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces, put in same large pot as chicken broth and remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour until tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Cook the pudding and milk. Cool and spread over white layer. Top with Cool Whip.

title: deviled clams
directions: Saute dry ingredients in oil until golden brown.
Put celery, clams and broth in blender.
Chop well.
Mix in bowl with sauteed mixture.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Stuff into oiled clam shells.
(Shells can be washed and reused.)
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until golden and bubbly.
Makes approximately 5 to 6 dozen.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients into a quart jar; screw lid on tightly and shake like the dickens.
Chill.
A blender works quite well if you have one.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups milk in top of double boiler.
Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Add remaining milk to paste and pour into hot milk.
Cook until thickened.
Beat egg yolks.
Pour small amount of hot mixture into yolks.
Stir, then add to milk mixture.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut.
Cool and pour into a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made of 4 tablespoons sugar and beaten egg whites.
Put meringue on top of pie; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: shrimp in angel hair pasta casserole
directions: With 1 tablespoon butter, grease a 12 x 8-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, half and half, yogurt, Swiss cheese, Feta cheese, parsley, basil and oregano.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 of the pasta on bottom of prepared pan.
Cover with salsa.
Add 1/2 of the shrimp.
Cover with remaining pasta.
Spread egg mixture over pasta and top with remaining shrimp.
Sprinkle Jack cheese over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Let stand 10 minutes.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef until done and drain. Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixed well. Heat until hot.

title: polish dish
directions: Cook cabbage, kielbasa and noodles.
Combine rest of ingredients and saute with oil.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until cream cheese is melted.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill until firm.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add juice; add apricots, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until set.
In double boiler, mix sugar, flour, egg, juice and butter.
Cook until thick, then cool.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Spread on top of Jell-O.
If desired, put nuts or cheese on top.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Put cabbage leaves in boiling water for about 10 minutes; drain.
Roll meat mixture in cabbage leaves; put in pan.
(Use water to cool them in.)
Pour 1 can Campbell's tomato soup over them; cook for 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Mix water, corn meal, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve from dish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables and combine.
Add remaining ingredients and stir into vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugars, salt and milk.
Cook to 240°, soft ball.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon several minutes until thick and creamy and gloss disappears.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch pan.

title: fruited cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients except mayonnaise and cream.
Chill. Just before serving, blend mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Toss dressing and salad.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix well.
Freeze for 2 hours; stir.
Let set in freezer for 24 hours.
Serve in small glasses (old fashion) or paper cups with a spoon.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp and celery in a bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise, mixed with lemon juice and onion.
Add cool rice and mix with fork.
Chill.
Very good second day.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with tomato wedges.

title: slow cooker company casserole
directions: Mix rice with melted butter or margarine in cooker.
Stir to coat rice thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients, except slivered almonds and some green onions to sprinkle over top.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
(High:
2 to 3 hours.)

title: sunny delight punch
directions: Heat oven to 350°. With serrated knife, trim ends from bread (save ends for snacking or bread crumbs). Cut bread into 1/4-inch thick slices. Arrange bread slices on 2 baking sheets. Brush oil over both sides of bread. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake in 350° oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden. Remove sheets from oven; turn slices over. Return to oven; bake 3 to 4 minutes or until golden and crusty. Let cool.

title: mexican hamburgers
directions: Brown pork in oil until done.
Add garlic, flours, chopped chilies, jalapeno pepper and canned tomatoes.
Simmer until flavors blend.
Brown hamburger, seasoned with salt, in separate skillet until done.
Serve on flour or corn tortilla with layer of burger meat, layer of pork mixture, lettuce, fresh tomatoes and topped with cheese.
Nacho chips may be substituted.

title: banana chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk and vegetable oil.
Stir just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips, mashed bananas and nuts.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 14 muffins.

title: black velvet torte
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Lightly grease 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Melt chocolate chips and milk in a saucepan.
Mix Bisquick, chocolate, eggs and oil 3 minutes with a mixer.
Pour into cake pans and cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix sugar into the whip topping.
When cake is done, split layers.
Put frozen strawberries between second and third layers.
Put whip cream between remaining layers.
Put remaining whip cream on the sides of cake and put remaining strawberries on the top of the cake.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Mix together with remaining ingredients and put in cupcake papers and freeze until frozen, then put the salad in a Tupperware container to store in the freezer.
Keeps a long time, unless you eat it.
Makes 18 servings.

title: refreshing smoothie
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Whirl until smooth.
Makes 2 servings at 195 calories per serving and 1 gram fat.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Whisk together eggs, flour and soda. Add chillies, cheese and half and half.
Lightly spray quiche pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: Flavor and sweeten to taste.
Mix all together and set in icebox several hours.
Can be made the day before serving.
Just before serving, fold in 1 cup of nuts.
Serves 12 people.

title: meal in one casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice (like you are making scalloped potatoes).
Peel carrots and slice thin (like potatoes).
Parboil both potatoes and carrots in separate pans.
Drain when almost done.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Now put a layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of pan.
Then add potatoes; add another layer of sauce, then put the layer of carrots on top and cover with sauce. Bake in 350° oven until warmed through.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and Crisco together.
Add all other ingredients and mix until creamy.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours and 10 minutes.

title: all sugar-free dessert
directions: Mix lime jello in 1 can of applesauce.
Mix raspberry jello in the other can of applesauce.
Put a layer of graham crackers on the bottom of dish.
Then put lime jello and applesauce mixture next.
Put another layer of graham crackers.
Then put a layer of the raspberry jello and applesauce mixture.
Top with Cool Whip. May put some Sweet'N Low in applesauce.

title: creole-style flounder(serves 6)
directions: Cook green pepper and onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, thyme and bay leaf.
Simmer gently for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf. Arrange fish in lightly greased, shallow baking pan.
Season with additional salt and pepper.
Spoon sauce over fillets.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Stir peas, if used, into rice.
Serve fish over beds of fluffy rice.
Contains 258 calories per serving.

title: ruth ann's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix soups, enchilada sauce and milk.
Add both mixtures.
Heat to a boil.
Pour over Doritos.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sausage bread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl, add salt, pepper, bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Mix and let stand for 20 minutes.
Fry sausage and fold into egg mixture.
Roll dough, spread mixture on top.
Roll up and brush top with beaten egg, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate dreams
directions: Mix together in a bowl the Quaker oats and cocoa.
In a pan on stove mix 1/2 cup evaporated milk, sugar and butter.
Bring to soft boil stage.
Mix into bowl with oats and cocoa.
Drop onto wax paper by spoonful and allow to cool.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Let set 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Put in container and put in freezer.

title: grandma's ranger cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, oats and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: it's a very good cake
directions: Mix together cake, pudding mixes, oil, water, eggs and vanilla (1 teaspoon).
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar, nuts and vanilla.

title: squirrel or chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken or squirrels with salt and pepper until tender. When done, have at least 2 quarts broth left.

title: vegetarian stuffed peppers
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat, and saute onions, garlic, zucchini and tomatoes.
Combine rice and cheese and add to the vegetable mixture.
Stuff peppers with the vegetable mixture and replace pepper top.
Pour tomato juice into the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place peppers in casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: crown of chocolate
directions: Grease and line bottom and sides of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add beaten egg yolks and melted chocolate.
Mix.
With a clean bowl and beaters, beat egg whites until stiff. Fold in chocolate mixture and whipped cream.
Pour into pan and chill until firm. Serves 10 to 16.

title: magic cookie bars #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool; store loosely covered. Makes 24 bars.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Scoop out center of bread and fill with dip. Dip out with bread pieces.

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill a 5-quart crock-pot heaping full of chopped apples, quartered or smaller, no need to peel.
Tart apples are best. Pour sugar, cinnamon, cloves and salt over apples.
Lid won't fit tight at first, but settles down as apples cook.
Begin cooking on high and when bubbling good, put heat on low and cook all day or night, until thick and dark color.
Stir now and then.
If need be, blend a few seconds to soften peels.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: bacon-chestnut appetizers
directions: Wrap halved bacon slices around chestnuts.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Broil until bacon is done.

title: gran's blonde brownies
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Melt butter in saucepan; remove from heat.
Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Pour into a greased 10 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In 6 quart saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar, milk and boil (full) 5 minutes.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter, fluff and flour.
(Hint:
Fudge hardens quickly after flour is added.
Have to move quickly to get it in a pan to harden.)
Pour in pan and let set.
Use a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet to pour the fudge into.

title: green pickled tomatoes
directions: Cut into small pieces.
Cook in a large container.
When tomatoes change color from green to brown, pack in jars and seal. Never boil.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Pour all ingredients except fruit into a bowl and mix well or until smooth.
Pour into baking dish and spread evenly.
The dough needs to be just soft enough to spread with a spoon.
Pour fruit gently over dough.
Do not stir dough.
Sprinkle 1/4 to 1 cup sugar over fruit; sprinkle with ground cinnamon and cloves.
Dot with butter.
Do not stir!
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix onion soup mix and rice together in a casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Stir.
Put chicken on mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours to brown chicken.
Remove lid for last few minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, stir in dressing and serve at once.

title: pop's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine. Roll out like biscuits, saving some of biscuit mix to work with. Melt 1/2 of margarine and coat top and bottom of each biscuit. Bake at 425° until done. Melt 1/2 stick butter and brush the top.

title: challah(communion bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/2 cup warm water. Let stand 5 minutes. Combine oil and next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Add yeast mixture and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth. Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. (Dough should be sticky.)
Cover dough and let rest 10 minutes.

title: grandma doris' german meat loaf with sweet and sour onion sauce
directions: Mix meat loaf ingredients well; form 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, approximately.
"Why waste perfectly good hot oven; make two and freeze one for later."

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Place cream cheese in a medium bowl; microwave at Medium (50%) until softened, 1 to 2 minutes, stirring once.
Shred crabmeat; stir into cream cheese with remaining ingredients.
Microwave at Medium (50%) until dip is heated through, 4 to 7 minutes or heat in a small crock-pot and keep stirring until mixed.
Serve with crackers.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix well, pineapple, Jell-O and hot water.
Refrigerate until just set.
Whip together sour cream and Cool Whip; add nuts. Flake in Jell-O mixture and mix well.
Can be put in mold, if desired.
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Place butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; microwave at High 45 seconds or until melted.
Stir in sugar, garlic salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts; toss gently to coat well.
Microwave at High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Let stand until cooled, stirring often.
Yields 4 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes to equal 3 cups.
Mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla. Spread in a greased, very shallow baking dish or heavy cookie sheet.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare 12 cupcake holders.
Mix dry ingredients.
Fold in milk, oil and egg.
Mix well.
Add blueberries after ingredients are well mixed.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 18 to 20 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash apples.
Cut into large pieces and put in melted butter. Add water.
Cover and fry until apples are tender.
Takes about 15 minutes.

title: papa's chicken
directions: Put all in cooking bag and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Hollow out bread loaf.
Put dip in bread.
Use bread chunks for dippers.

title: holly candies
directions: Melt marshmallows in a double boiler with the stick of margarine.
Add the food coloring and cereal.
Stir quickly to cover all flakes.
Drop from boiler onto greased waxed paper. While hot, put 3 or 4 red hot candies on to look like holly berries.

title: 3 soup beef dinner
directions: Rice can be substituted for noodles.

title: kick off chili
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, brown the ground beef and ground pork sausage with garlic and onion.
Add bell pepper and smoke sausage chunks.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer over medium heat. Reduce to low and drain fat.
Blend in spices and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in kidney beans.
In a bowl, blend some of the bean liquid with cornmeal to consistency similar to pancake batter.
Mix with chili and simmer another 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Add rest of ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack and cool.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 3 eggs well (will be thick).
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: connie's pull aparts
directions: Set dough on counter for 10 minutes.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch slices, then 1/4 of 1/6.
Grease Bundt pan.
Put pieces in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding over.
Melt oleo and add sugar.
Add nuts.
Pour over dough.
Let set on counter overnight. In the morning, bake for 30 minutes at 350° in preheated oven. Remove from oven and set overnight.

title: reese's balls
directions: Mix well.
Knead with hands.
Roll into balls.
Chill.
Dip into chocolate.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler. Insert toothpicks into balls and dip in chocolate.

title: frank and potato bake
directions: In saucepan, stir milk into flour and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly until a smooth paste is made.
Put potatoes and wieners which have been sliced around 1/4 inch thick into a 2-quart casserole.
Reserve 3 or 4 wieners for decorating top of casserole.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; arrange reserved wieners in pinwheel on top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes until brown.
Decorate with parsley.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beating after each. Add coconut, flour, cocoa, vanilla and nuts. Mix well with spoon. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. As soon as cake is done, remove from oven. Spread marshmallows on top. Let cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup, eggs, salt and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9 or 10-inch pie shell.
Bake for 5 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm (about 40 minutes).

title: ruth's pudding dessert
directions: Beat pudding and milk well. Mix ice cream well with pudding. Add Dream Whip to ice cream mixture. Pour over cracker crumbs (save a few crumbs to sprinkle over top).
Refrigerate.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a saucepan, saute onions slowly over low heat until transparent.
Add potatoes; cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add corn and liquid to potatoes.
Add a few shakes of pepper and heat thoroughly.

title: cheese stix
directions: Cut crust off bread and cut into strips (electric knife works well).
Beat cheese, margarine and egg with mixer.
Brush bread with mixture and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
(Spraying cookie sheet with Pam works well.)

title: mixed salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water; add marshmallows and cool.
Add cheese, celery, pineapple, dressing, nuts and whipped cream.
Sprinkle strawberry jello over the top.

title: citrus lizz
directions: Combine all juices in large pitcher.
Add ginger ale and ice. Pour into 6 tall glasses and garnish with orange wedges.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until it foms a soft boil.
Add flavor (vanilla) and coconut, then pour on a greased platter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients except whipped cream.
Beat whipping cream in separate bowl until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Cure for one hour (let set in refrigerator).
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix eggs.
Add sugar and salt, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in corn syrup and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Stir in pecan halves.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blue cheese biscuito
directions: Cream the cheese and butter.
Mix in flour and coarsely chopped nuts.
Take teaspoons of mixture and form into balls.
Roll balls in finely chopped nuts and bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes. Serve cold.

title: charleston she-crab soup
directions: Melt butter; add crab meat and saute for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cream, milk and seasoning.
Thicken with cracker crumbs and let stand over lowest possible heat for a few minutes or until heated through thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Add sherry just before serving soup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggless spice cake
directions: Boil for 3 minutes the sugar, shortening, salt, cloves, water, raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Let cool.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: ambrosia dessert
directions: Drain fruit well and mix together.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil for 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal and stir for 1 minute.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: shells and shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.

title: vegetarian pasta a la greque
directions: In large saucepan, cook zucchini and onion in hot oil for 5 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, mint, dill weed and salt.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes.

title: white vanilla fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, evaporated milk and salt into saucepan and bring to boil over medium heat.
Once mixture is boiling, cook 10 to 11 minutes or to 225° on a candy thermometer.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, heat soup and broccoli until thawed.
In a 10-inch skillet, pour 1 tablespoon oil.
Cook carrots and onion until lightly browned.
Reduce heat to low and add 1/4 cup water. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until veggies are tender.
Remove from pan, set aside in a bowl.
In same skillet pour 3 tablespoons oil.
Cook mushrooms until brown and all liquid is evaporated. Stir in carrot mixture.
While veggies are cooking prepare noodles as suggested.
Drain.
In medium size bowl, mix Mozzarella, Ricotta and eggs.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer the following:
1 cup broccoli sauce, 1/2 noodles over sauce, 1/2 cheese mixture, all of carrot mixture and 1/2 of remaining sauce. Top with remaining noodles, cheese mixture, then sauce.
Bake 45 minutes, let stand 10 minutes.
Serve.
Serves 10.
Each serving is 465 calories, 25 grams fat, 104 mg cholesterol and 615 mg sodium.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 3 minutes after it comes to a rolling boil.
Pour cooked mixture over the remaining ingredients and stir 3 minutes or longer.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt until crumbly.
Mix beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Add liquid mixture to flour mixture; stir until soft dough forms.
Makes approximately 5 single crusts, depending on thickness.

title: frozen berry jam
directions: Wash, stem and crush enough berries to make 4 level cups of fruit.
Slowly sift in the pectin.
Stir vigorously.
Set aside for 30 minutes with occasional stirring.
Add the corn syrup and mix well.
Measure the sugar into the container and gradually stir this into crushed berries.
Warm mixture to 100° and it will hasten the sugar to dissolve.

title: broccoli-rice hot dish
directions: Melt margarine; add rest of ingredients and place in casserole dish or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Top with small jar of Cheez Whiz. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple supreme bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Cook for 45 to 55 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: spinach and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large saucepan, cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Stir in soup, ham and mustard. Pour into 9 x 9 inch baking pan. Top with eggs. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through. Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well and add nutmeg, cinnamon and sweet potatoes.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Add topping.

title: macaroni chicken salad
directions: Gradually add macaroni and 1 tablespoon salt to rapidly boiling water so that water continues to boil. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain in colander. Rinse with cold water.
Drain again.

title: 300 oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add.
Mix everything very well. You can roll dough into walnut-sized balls and dip tops in white sugar, or drop by teaspoon or use an ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup measure to make giant cookies.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hush puppies with corn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add corn, onion, egg and 2 tablespoons oil; stir well. Drop batter by level tablespoonful into deep, hot oil (370°). Cook a few at a time, turning once. Fry 3 to 5 minutes until hush puppies are golden brown. Drain well on paper towels. Yield: about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend Oreos (a few at a time) in a blender.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix 2 (3 ounce) packages pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Add small bowl mixture.
In flowerpot, layer 1/3 Oreos, 1/2 mixture, 1/3 Oreos, etcetera.
End with Oreos on top. Garnish with gummy worms.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and margarine to crumb size for topping.
Line pan with pastry.
Cut apples into 1/8-inch pieces and place in pan.
Sprinkle the sugar/cinnamon mix over them.
Sprinkle crumb topping over all. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mozzarella salad
directions: Remove tomatoes from marinade; cut into thin strips. Combine all ingredients, except spinach and olive oil, in a medium bowl. Add olive oil to cover. Marinate at least 2 hours. To serve, arrange spinach on chilled platter. Pour cheese mixture over spinach. Serves 10 to 12.

title: barbecue short ribs
directions: Precook ribs in salt, pepper and water for 2 hours.
Barbecue over slow coals 15 to 20 minutes.
Baste in sauce and serve with remaining sauce.

title: pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Add cucumbers and let soak 50 minutes.
Put dill and 2 grape leaves in bottom of each jar to be used.
(Add a small piece of garlic if desired.)
Pack cucumbers in jars tightly.
Now reheat the liquid. Pour over the cucumbers and seal.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover; chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with tines of fork dipped in granulated sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool
1 to 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.
Cool completely.
Store tightly.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and put into a baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips or corn flakes.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: nutty buddy pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix cream cheese, milk, xxx sugar, peanut butter and Cool Whip and pour into pie shells.
Lightly swirl chocolate syrup over pies, making thin lines all over top. Sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze.
Makes three pies and will keep in the freezer for several weeks.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs in mixing bowl until fluffy.
Sift in remaining dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in carrots and pecans.

title: puppy chow for kids
directions: Melt all ingredients, then mix 8 cups of cereal.
Pour into a plastic bag with 3 cups of confectioners sugar.
Shake well until cereal is coated.

title: thick and chewy monster cookies
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar in large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir in oats and mix dough until stiff.
Stir in candies, etc.
Make into large balls spaced apart to allow cookies to spread to their "monster" size.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 13 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Cool on sheets 5 minutes, then remove.

title: chicken and wild rice soup
directions: Cook chicken and cut up. In remaining broth, boil wild rice until it starts to pop (about 45 minutes to an hour). Add as many bouillon cubes as desired; add salt and pepper. Add onion and garlic powder, poultry seasoning, onion, carrots, and celery. Cook until vegetables are tender. Add chicken to soup; add 1 to 2 c. Half and Half for color; thicken with corn starch or flour. Adjust seasoning to your taste.

title: almond brickle dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
In small saucepan, combine almonds, 1/3 cup sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, honey and 1 tablespoon milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, about 9 to 11 minutes, stirring constantly; boil an additional 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; set aside.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, eggs, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Mix well; set aside.
Evenly spread 3/4 cup sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer with 3 noodles, 2 cups cheese mixture and 3/4 cup sauce.
Repeat layers twice.
Top with 3 noodles, remaining sauce and reserved cheese.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Can be made ahead.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook together in an iron skillet the sugar, water, Karo, peanuts and salt.
Cook until peanuts start popping big.
Remove from heat and add 2 teaspoons soda.
Beat good and pour into 3 tin plates which have been buttered.
When cool, bend plate to break the candy.

title: cappuccino parfait
directions: Combine gelatin and 1/2 cup coffee in a small bowl; let stand 1 minute.
Heat remaining coffee to a simmer in small saucepan. Add gelatin mixture and sugar to hot coffee.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin and sugar dissolve.
Remove from heat; stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze until almost frozen.
Spoon mixture into blender or food processor.
Add liqueur; process until smooth.
Return to pan; freeze until firm.
Spoon into parfait glasses; serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Spray pan with pam, place dough balls in
pan. Mix all sauce ingredients & bring to a boil pour sauce over balls. Leave in oven overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 min. Invert pan & rolls in plate, sauce will cover rolls.

title: danish puffs(for breakfast)
directions: (Can substitute with rich shortening.)

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Set aside, then beat egg whites until very stiff.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and Crisco very good. Add egg yolks, 1 at a time.

title: broiled scallops
directions: Combine oil, catsup, garlic, salt and paprika.
Stir well. Add scallops and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Remove scallops from marinade; place in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour enough marinade over scallops to coat, but not cover (about 1 cup).
Broil 2 minutes.
Turn scallops over and broil 2 minutes or until done.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time and beat after each addition.
Add flour and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased tube pan 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Pat graham cracker crust in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and 1/2 Cool Whip; spread over cheese.
Add milk to instant pudding; mix with mixer and spread in pan.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar. Mix rest of ingredients except oats. Bring to a boil. Pour over oats. Stir well; drop onto wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: Combine ground pecans, wafer crumbs, rum and honey in bowl. Chill for 20 minutes.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into ball.
Store in airtight containers.
Roll in confectioners sugar just before serving.
May substitute 1/2 cup orange juice and teaspoon of grated orange peel for rum.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add egg, oil, flour and salt to taste.
Mix well and roll into biscuits.
Let rise.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, salt and red pepper together; set aside.
Coat chicken with melted margarine.
Dip into dry ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam and bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in with Marshmallow Fluff.
Dip with strawberries, peaches or other desired fruits.

title: couscous with raisins and red peppers
directions: In a saucepan with tight fitting lid, heat olive oil.
Add onions and red peppers.
Stir until wilted, not brown.
Add water, raisins and spices.
Remove from heat and add couscous.
Stir well.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Add butter and fluff.

title: apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and add apples, walnuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook, stirring 4 minutes or until tender. Let cool.
Separate dough into triangles.
Roll out and place 1 tablespoon of apple mixture on each crescent triangle.
Roll up each crescent and gently pinch edges together.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Scrape carrots and cut thin strips julienne style.
Cook carrots in saucepan about 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain. Put carrots in baking dish.
In a bowl, combine 1/4 cup of the liquid (carrots were cooked in), onion, horseradish, mayonnaise, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Pour over carrots.
Top with bread crumbs and butter. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: Make like pie crust. Spread peanut butter onto rolled dough. Roll in a round roll and chill. Slice thin.

title: 3 months pickles
directions: Small or medium cucumbers work best.

title: sugar-free sugar pecans
directions: Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in pecans and remove from heat.
Allow pecans to rest in sugar water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and cool.

title: glazed french bread
directions: Divide dough in half. Roll portion of dough into a 13 x 8-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface. Roll dough jellyroll fashion, starting at long edge, pressing firmly to eliminate all air pockets; pinch ends and seams to seal. Place loaf, seam side down, on a greased baking sheet. Repeat procedure with remaining portion of dough. Cover and let rise in a warm (85°), draft free place about 45 minutes or until double in size. Carefully make diagonal slits about 1/4-inch deep down the lengths of the loaves using a sharp knife. Combine egg and milk, beating with a fork until blended; gently brush over loaves. Sprinkle each loaf with desired seeds. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until loaves sound hollow when tapped. Cool on wire racks.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Combine white sugar and cinnamon.
Coat pieces of biscuits with sugar mixture.
Layer coated biscuits in greased Bundt pan with chopped nuts.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a medium bowl, blend mayonnaise, sugar and milk; mix well. Add vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli, carrots, Bac*Os and Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate for at least an hour.
Stir again before serving.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well to the consistency desired.
Chill and serve on plate of lettuce leaves as dip for tostadas or sandwich filling, or simply with chips.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all together. Make into patties and fry in oil until golden brown.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine together eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell after mixing well.
Arrange the pecan halves on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center of pie is firm.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and let stand overnight or for 2 hours minimum before serving.

title: rinktum pitty
directions: Cream butter and flour; add cream and tomato juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil; cook until thick.
Add grated cheese.
Serve on toast.
Serves 4.

title: farina squares
directions: Heat milk and sugar on stove.
Add farina to milk gradually and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add egg and almond extract.
Add mixture to a lightly greased shallow pan and refrigerate.
When mixture is set, cut into squares.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (vegetables) together.
Add Fritos and low-calorie dressing just before serving.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts like pie dough and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool. While crust is baking, mix the following: powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Place in cooled crust, then mix together cold milk and instant pudding.
Layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: okra fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, scrubbing with vegetable brush.	Dry and grease well with
bacon
drippings.
Place
in shallow pan and bake at 375° until done (soft to touch).

title: apple torte(serves 10)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and cook until clear.
Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, brown sugar and warm oleo; mix together well. Reserve one cup of crumbs for the top, pur rest in bottom of (13 x 9-inch) pan for crust.
Slice apples over mixture in bottom of pan, cover with sauce and sprinkle with the reserved crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: holubky(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Scald cabbage leaves; set aside to cool.
Combine beef, rice, chopped onion, salt, pepper and milk; mix well.
Place tablespoon of meat mixture on cabbage leaf and roll.
Place cabbage rolls in large kettle; cover with extra cabbage and sauerkraut and juice. If you want more flavor, add an extra can of kraut juice, tomatoes and onion.
Cover; cook over low heat for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: green bean salad
directions: Cook green beans in boiling water with salt until tender, but still crunchy.
Cool.
Cut tomato in wedges and slice onion thinly.
Pour olive oil and vinegar over beans.
Mix beans, tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: polish sausage appetizer
directions: Cut sausage in 1-inch thick slices.
Add beer; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Blend in vinegar, mustard and horseradish.
Add to sausage.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Serve warm.
Better made a day or 2 in advance.

title: chunky style ham and bean soup
directions: Use no salt.
Boil potatoes, celery and onion until soft. Save water for soup. Add the Great Northern beans to the potatoes and water.
Add more water.
Break chunks of ham into soup. Add parsley and pepper. Do not add salt because of ham. Add more water, if necessary. Simmer on low until hot. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Use for summer picnics or on a cold winter day.
Serves 6 or more.

title: pastry for a cream pie
directions: Put all ingredients in pie pan.
Mix with a fork until formed into a ball.
Pat out by hand, working the dough up side of pan. Prick crust.
Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Use a skillet and a 9-inch unbaked pie shell; bake in a 375° oven for 35 or 40 minutes.
Fry the sausage and drain well; cook the onion and pepper in the same skillet, using 2 tablespoons of the sausage fat.
Combine the sausage, cheese mixture.
Cool a few minutes.
Press the mixture into the bottom and the sides of the unbaked pie shell.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over the first mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until nicely browned and the filling is set.

title: toasted almond and poppy seed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy!

title: millionaire pie
directions: In a large bowl combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and salt. Beat until light.
Stir in vanilla.
Drain pineapple and add pineapple with chopped pecans, mix well.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie shells.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: max's merry christmas nog
directions: Separate eggs, setting aside the whites in another bowl.
Beat egg yolks and add the sugar until creamy.
Add milk and avoset to mixture continuing to stir.
Add brandy, rum and bourbon.
Beat the egg whites in another bowl until stiff and then spoon mixture into the eggnog.
Pour into glasses and dash with nutmeg.

title: corn chex mix
directions: Mix the brown sugar, corn syrup and butter in a 300° frying pan.
Melt and cook 5 minutes. Add Corn Chex and peanuts. Mix well.
Pour on buttered pan. Cool.
Break into chunks.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix vinegar and dry mustard and let stand overnight.
Beat eggs and stir into mixture; add sugar and salt.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cook until it coats the spoon, stirring constantly.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into lightly greased iron skillet.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat 1 minute after each egg. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place uncooked rice in baking pan, large.
Add and mix the cream soups and water.
Place uncooked chicken on top of rice and soup mixture. Bake at 400° approximately 1 hour.

title: creamy jello jigglers
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Cool to room temperature. Add milk.
Mix in the pudding with a wire whisk.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and cut.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix sugar, water and lemon peel.
Place in refrigerator to make syrup.
Put 1/4 cup syrup in glass.
Add lemon juice and additional water with ice cubes.
May add slice of lemon for extra flavor.

title: caribbean shrimp
directions: Combine the onion with two tablespoons of water; set aside to soften, about 10 minutes.
In a large skillet, heat the butter until hot.
Add the green pepper and onion; cook, stirring, until almost crisp and tender (about 3 minutes).
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, sugar, allspice, salt and ground red pepper, breaking up the tomatoes with a spoon.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook and stir until pink, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in the lime juice. Remove the bay leaf before serving.
Serve on steamed rice, if desired.
Serves four.

title: sugar-free cheese cake snack
directions: Put gelatine in blender and pour in hot water and blend.
Add the rest of the ingredients and blend well.
Pour into lightly buttered pie plate or 8-inch square pan or dish.
Top with cinnamon, lightly sprinkled.
Slice into 4 slices, each is equal to 1 1/2 milk and 1 fruit.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken-vegetable pizza
directions: Dice chicken and sprinkle with chicken seasoning; cook in a nonstick skillet until done. Chop and microwave pepper, onions and broccoli for 2 minutes. Spread crust with Ranch dressing; top with vegetables, chicken, tomato and cheeses.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: galumpki's(ukrainian stuffed cabbage)
directions: Core cabbage, parboil and peel whole leaves off.
Set aside. In large skillet, saute small cubed salt pork and one large onion (diced) until salt pork is golden brown and onion translucent.
Put hamburg and rice into bowl; add salt pork and onion mixture and salt and pepper.
Mix well.

Roll in cabbage leaves and set aside. In large pot put garlic, 1 large onion (chopped), 1 cup salt pork chunks and 1 can tomato puree, then stack cabbage rolls tight. Dump stewed tomatoes between layers and on top.
Cover.
Cook over low heat 3 to 4 hours or until done.

title: korean barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the soy sauce, sugar, sesame oil, pepper, diced onion, diced green onion and chopped garlic.
Use this sauce to marinate thinly sliced beef (rump roast), chicken or pork chops for 2 to 3 hours.
Grill or broil.
Serve over white rice.

title: leche flan
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the 3 to 4 tablespoons brown sugar. Immediately pour evenly into a loaf pan or 9-inch pie pan.
Set aside to cool and caramelize.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Coat large skillet with oil.
Add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: lupe salad
directions: Dice tomatoes, chop onions, celery and peppers; mix together salt and pepper.
Squeeze the juice from the lemons and pour over mixture.
It may take more or less lemon juice.
It's mainly to taste.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and you will have a good cake (Proverbs 23:14).
Bake at 325° in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 2 loaves in shallow baking pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done. Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix all together. Shape into balls.
Roll in sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Top with chocolate kisses and return to oven for 1 minute.

title: carter clusters
directions: Cook on low to melt butter then turn to medium high and boil for 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Add 1 tsp vanilla, 6 oz semi-sweet chocolate chips and 3 c roasted peanuts.
Drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.

title: salem cross oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and cool to lukewarm.
To this, add butter, salt, molasses and dissolved yeast.
Mix in the eggs and gradually add the flour, adding more if necessary.
Knead for 10 minutes on floured board.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled.
Shape into 2 loaves. Spread tops with butter and lightly sprinkle with oats.
Cover and let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: weight watchers mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O (dry) into Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese and oranges.
Chill until set.
May easily be doubled.
