title: marinara sauce(on the healthy side)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook onion, carrots and garlic in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Add undrained tomatoes, sugar, salt, oregano, pepper and red pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti, linguine or other pasta.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Brown meat and onion, add water, cook until almost ready.
Add all vegetables, cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Add beans, simmer for 20 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Soak overnight in cooking pot or boil for 2 minutes and soak for 1 hour.
Bring to boil with the bay leaf, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, noting the time.
Meanwhile, heat oil in frying pan in medium-high heat.
Saute onion for 2 to 3 minutes, then add green pepper, garlic, salt, cumin and cayenne and saute a few minutes more.
When beans have been simmering 20 minutes or so, add vegetables.
Simmer about another 20 minutes, adding soy sauce toward end.
Serve each bowl garnished with chopped fresh parsley.

title: italian fruit salad(makes about 3 quarts)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until done.
Rinse and drain.
Cook juice of pineapple and oranges, 3/4 cup sugar, eggs and lemon juice.
Cook and stir constantly over low heat until mixture boils.
Mix macaroni and sauce together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, add pineapple, oranges, cherries (cut in half) and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: pasta house tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini until half done; strain and return to pan. Add cream, margarine, mushrooms, peas and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly until tortellini is fully done.
Remove from heat and stir in Parmesan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into shallow baking dish.
Roll Cheez-Its crackers to crust.
Put on top and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Cut oleo in dry ingredients until crumbly.
Press firmly into sides and bottom of pie plate.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes. Cool and fill with desired filling (suggestions are lemon filling, any fruit thickened or milk pudding).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat with electric mixer.
Beat until blended; smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.

title: two hour pan rolls
directions: Mix together warm water, yeast, sugar and salt, then add shortening.
Mix well, then add flour in gradually and stirring well.
Knead dough about 20 times and have soft workable dough. Place in large bowl; place in warm area and let rise 1 hour. Punch down.
Let rise 1 more hour.
Place in muffin pans or make rolls as desired.
Lightly brush with melted shortening.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° until nicely browned.
Brush each roll with butter.
Recipe can be used as dinner rolls, cinnamon or sticky rolls.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Cut crusts off bread and roll each slice flat.
Combine cheeses, egg and mayonnaise.
Spread mixture on slices.
Place one piece of asparagus in each.
Roll up and slice in thirds.
Dip in melted butter.
Arrange on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or freeze on cookie sheet, then bag and save for future use.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix by hand the first 3 ingredients until well mixed.
Add nuts and vanilla; mix until it will hold shape.
Make into small, flattened balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll or shake in powdered sugar while warm and again when cool.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Combine 1 cup of sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add water.
Add pineapple and cook until thick.
Pour mixture over egg yolks and beat.
Return to saucepan.
Cook until thick, about 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Fold hot mixture into meringue of egg whites, whipped with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Chill and serve plain or with whipped topping.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and beat Crisco, brown sugar, granulated sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add the hot water and vanilla; beat.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda; add to first mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Mix in soup and tuna.
Place in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 - 30 minutes, until bread crumbs are brown.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions and layer in Pyrex bowl.
Cover with soup mixed with almonds.
Sprinkle with cornflakes dotted with margarine. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oriental meat balls
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and salt.
Cook slowly. Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup pineapple juice and add to sauce.
Add meat balls and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining pineapple juice as needed.
Just before serving, add the pineapple, tomato and green pepper.
Cook until heated through.
(Do not overcook.)
Serve to the side of rice.

title: best ever pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place in preheated oven.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and set on wire rack to cool.
Yields 8 servings.

title: american spaghetti sauce
directions: Season ground meat; cook until brown.
Take off heat.
Finely chop celery, onion and pepper.
Put in skillet with margarine. Pour can of tomato soup on top; let simmer about 10 to 15 minutes. Combine with meat.
Cook on low heat about 3 hours, or until real tender.
(Usually cook in double boiler; the secret in the taste is slow cooking.) When the sauce is almost cooked, add the cheese. Cook 1 pound of spaghetti; drain water.
Add spaghetti to sauce. If your family likes olives and mushrooms, add small bottle of each.
Serves 12.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed until creamy (the butter will become a lighter yellow color; this is an important step, as the job of the mixer is to incorporate air into the margarine so the cake will rise.
It will take approximately 7 minutes, depending on the power of your mixer.)
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until light and fluffy (again, the time will vary and butter will turn to a fluffy white).
Add eggs, 1 at a time beating just until yellow yolk disappears, add flour to creamed mixture alternating with whipping cream.
Beat at low speed just until blended after each addition.
The batter should be smooth and bits of flour should be well incorporated; to rid batter of lumps, stir gently with a rubber spatula.
Stir in extracts, pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
(Use vegetable shortening or butter to grease the pan, getting every nook and cranny covered.) Bake at 300 for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a long wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: memere bernard's grape nut pudding
directions: Heat milk and Grape-Nuts.
Combine sugar, salt and eggs.
Add Grape-Nuts/milk mixture and vanilla.
Pour into buttered ovenproof dish.
Place dish into another pan with 1-inch of water in the bottom and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, checking after 3/4 of an hour.

title: chilly day chili
directions: In large pan, saute onions and green pepper in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce, ketchup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add partially drained red kidney beans. Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: rice with black beans
directions: Cook and stir onion in hot oil until tender.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: yogurt-sour cream chive dressing for baked potato
directions: Stir together sour cream and remaining ingredients.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar gradually until meringue is stiff.
Fold in other ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch Pyrex pan for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.
Serves 6. Top with scoop of ice cream.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a saucepan.
Add egg, milk, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Cool completely, then add 1/2 cup mayonnaise (regular or light) and 2 tablespoons yellow mustard.
This keeps in the refrigerator for several months.
This is an excellent dressing for potato or macaroni salad.

title: sweet and sour stew
directions: Coat meat with flour mixture.
Brown well in large skillet. Combine catsup, water, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onion.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and cook until meat and carrots are tender (about 1 hour).

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix cream cheese well.
Add pineapple.
Mix well.
Add fruit cocktail, then fold in cream which has been whipped.
Add the sugar to taste.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook beef until tender.
Pull apart in bite size pieces, reserving juice.

Saute onion, garlic and flour in margarine. Add the roast beef, chicken soup, mushroom soup and juice from the roast beef. Bring everything to boiling point, then simmer 15 minutes. Stir in sour cream and serve over noodles.

title: quick russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until well blended.
Place in a covered container for storage.

title: birds nest(easy)
directions: Cut a hole in the middle of the piece of bread, large enough to contain the egg yolk.
Melt margarine in skillet and brown bread on one side.
Flip and carefully crack egg, dropping it into the hole so as not to break the yolk.
Cover skillet and simmer slowly until egg firms.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef together; drain well.
Add sauce.
Cook a few minutes; set aside.
Sprinkle flour on wax paper.
Roll one biscuit at a time, just big enough to fit in a muffin pan.
Place heaping spoonfuls of meat mixture into biscuits.
Sprinkle with a little onion, peppers, olives, mushrooms and peppers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° until biscuits are brown.

title: sunday-morning rolls
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix milk, eggs and cooled shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Combine remaining sugar, cinnamon and butter; spread over dough.
Roll as for jelly roll; seal edge.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together until foamy.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mix well.
When smooth, mix in apples and nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Frost with the frosting or Coconut Pecan Icing recipe.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine fruit juices with tea in large punch bowl.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Float ice cubes in punch; garnish with orange or lemon slices.
Approximate yield is 20 (6-ounce) servings.

title: sunny sherbet slush
directions: In large non-metal container, combine all juices and sherbet until well blended.
Cover and freeze.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery; separate and use tender inner stalks.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Mash cheese with fork; add salt, pepper, paprika, Worcestershire and enough mayonnaise to make of spreading consistency.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot liquid in a casserole or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add 7-Up and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: easy going minestrone(you can substitute your own vegetable preferences.)
directions: In Dutch oven or 4 quart saucepan, bring bouillon and water to boil; add macaroni and cook about 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender and vegetables are cooked.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve sprinkled with cheese. Serves 8.

title: noodle cluster candy
directions: Melt chips and add peanuts and noodles. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: fresh apple pies
directions: Combine flour and salt in medium bowl.
Combine oil and 2 tablespoons water.
Stir into flour mixture.
Add extra water only as needed.
Shape dough into a ball.
Roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Place pastry in 9-inch pie plate; trim and flute edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry shells with fork.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons apple juice, mixing well.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients, except apple slices, in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes or just until apples are tender.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and thickened.
Cool; spoon into pastry shell.
Dip apple slices in lemon juice; drain.
Garnish top of pie with apple slices.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: beef barbecue
directions: With fork tear chunks of beef apart.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; reduce heat to simmer and cook 20 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add candies.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: chicken surabaja
directions: You will also need 12 wooden or metal skewers.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in three 8-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: shrimp parmesan
directions: Boil and peel shrimp. Combine soups and water in small saucepan. Bring to a boil. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are hot. At the same time, in another pan, cook the fettuccini as directed on package. Drain fettuccini; put serving on plate and cover with shrimp sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Salt and pepper to taste. Serves 2.

title: the quik lite italian for "2"
directions: First Step:
Brown chicken with onions, mushrooms, spices and 1/4 cup water (not oil).
Cut chicken in cubes.

title: microwave munching peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in microwave and cook 7 to 8 minutes, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir well. Return to oven and cook an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Allow to cool 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on.
When cool, peel and cube.
Cut bacon and fry.
Brown onion in bacon grease.
Add vinegar, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add potatoes which have been salted.
Heat thoroughly in large frypan or large casserole in moderate oven.
Serve hot.

title: veggie grits
directions: Follow package directions to cook 1 c. grits in 4 c. water. Combine cooked grits with remaining ingredients except 1 c. of cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9 by 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375 degrees. Serve hot.

title: chili chip dip
directions: Drain hamburger and onions.
Add other ingredients, cheese last.
Simmer.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; add milk and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Melt margarine in ovenproof 10 inch nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook bell peppers and onion in margarine, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender. Beat eggs, salt and pepper in medium bowl. Stir in 1/2 c. cheese. Pour egg mixture over pepper mixture. Cover and cook over medium low heat 8 to 10 minutes or until eggs are set and light brown on bottom. Set oven control to broil. Broil frittata with top 4 to 6 inches from heat about 2 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into wedges. This has 4 grams carbohydrate.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse macaroni and set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Add macaroni and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a slightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden corn and chicken chowder
directions: Cook squash; scoop squash out of shell.
In 4-quart pan, heat oil; add onion, carrot, celery, garlic and bacon; cook 5 to 6 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add squash, soup, water and chicken; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes until vegetables are tender and flavors are blended.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir in eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Frost cake while warm.

title: taco bake
directions: In skillet cook, turkey, onions, bell peppers, and tomatoes until done and vegetables are tender.
Add chilies, taco seasoning, 1/2 tsp. salt, tomato sauce, and 1/2 can water.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes to blend flavors. Transfer to 9x13 inch greased pan. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix butter, flour, buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and dash of salt until smooth.
Pour batter evenly over cheese.
Bake at 450 degrees for 30 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In medium saucepan, cook pepper in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk, chicken and pimento.
Heat (preferably in double boiler), stirring occasionally.
Serve over baked pastry shells or toast points.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Beat well all ingredients and drop by spoon fulls into lightly oiled muffin tins, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Let rise, then bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: my best friend - braided bread
directions: Combine yeast, 1 1/2 cups flour, salt and sugar in a bowl. Pour in water and beat until smooth.
Mix in soft margarine, eggs, a pinch of saffron or a few drops of food coloring.
Slowly add enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.

title: 1-2-3 sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pinch off enough mixture to make 1-inch balls.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or roll out dough and cut into small biscuits and bake.
These freeze well.
Bake first and then reheat.
Makes 30.

title: chocolate brandy cookies
directions: Grate chocolate fine; set aside.
In a very large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, almonds, grated chocolate and brandy. Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour to liquid mixture, one cup at a time.
Mix thoroughly after each addition. Dough will be stiff.
For easier rolling, refrigerate dough.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and mash.
Add melted butter, sugar, beaten eggs, milk and flavorings.
Beat mixture with electric mixer to remove strings from potatoes. (Strings will wrap around beaters.)

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until most of water is absorbed; drain. Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 350°
in greased and floured 7 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour or a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crunchy green pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water to thaw.
Drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon bits.
Mix dressing, mustard and sour cream.
Pour over salad and toss gently.
Chill before serving.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Cut flour and margarine together; combine sour cream and egg yolk.
Blend into flour mixture to form soft dough.
Divide into equal parts.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: beefy mexican lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 can of French fried onions.
In bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1 cup of Cheddar cheese and eggs.
Place 3 tortillas on bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Overlap 6 tortillas around sides of baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture evenly in dish.
Top with 3 tortillas, then cheese mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place remaining onions in center of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.
Before serving, arrange tomatoes and lettuce around edge of casserole.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Drain well (1/2 hour) the pineapple.
Beat together powdered sugar, eggs and oleo.
Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix the soups in a dish, add the water stir until smooth. Add the rice and the orange juice.
Pour in greased 9x13 baking dish.
Arrange the chicken on top and put margarine on top of chicken (to keep it from drying out a lot).

title: winona's cauliflower-zucchini salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl and sprinkle with sugar.

title: fast and easy baked beans
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, add all ingredients.
Mix well. Cook on simmer for 20 minutes and enjoy.

title: chicken noodle tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove from broth. Cool, bone and cut into small pieces.
Strain broth.
Let cool and remove fat.
Reserve chicken broth.

title: spinach-shrimp quiche
directions: Place all ingredients, except eggs and half and half in plastic bag and shake with 2 tablespoons flour to coat everything. Beat eggs and half and half.
Add bag full of dry ingredients to egg mixture and stir only to moisten all ingredients. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mash bananas.
Add bananas and eggs to creamed butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add orange rind and nuts (optional).
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper sauce
directions: *You can use banana peppers, jalapeno peppers, or any other sweet or hot pepper of your choice.

title: homemade chili
directions: In a large frying pan, mix ground beef, onions and tomatoes. Cook until beef is done, stirring often.
Add in a large pot the beef, mixture, cooked macaroni, kidney beans, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Let boil 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat. Add tomato juice.
Reduce heat.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes. Serve.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Blanch cabbage; drain thoroughly and sprinkle with lemon juice to restore red color.
In small skillet, saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until translucent.
Add cabbage and simmer, tightly covered, in remaining butter and flour diluted with a few spoonfuls of beef broth or water for 5 minutes.
Test for seasoning and add more lemon juice if necessary (cabbage should be fairly dry).
Sprinkle with sugar; stir in apples and cook another 5 to 8 minutes until both cabbage and apples are tender.
Add additional broth or water if needed.

title: cranberry-orange-apricot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Combine first six ingredients, mixing well; set aside. Beat eggs and oil with wire whisk to blend thoroughly.
Mix in orange juice, water and orange peel.
Add dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Rub the slices of bread with garlic cloves.
Place 3 tomatoes and garlic in food processor and puree.
Remove to a large bowl, leaving some puree in the processor.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Take a fork and cut shortening into flour. Then add your milk. Roll out on cutting board and cut. Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: kahlua number 3
directions: Mix coffee and sugar; add boiling water, simmer for 4 minutes. Skim top.
Add vanilla.
Let cool and add vodka.
If too strong, add vanilla.
If too thick, add water.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and other dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix on low speed with hand mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat three more minutes on high.
Stir in remaining flour.
Grease two loaf pans and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon batter into pans.
Sprinkle top of batter with cornmeal.
Cover with a clean towel and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. When cool, slice thin and toast.

title: turkey scallop
directions: Arrange alternate layers of 1 1/2 cups crumbs and diced turkey in casserole, seasoning each layer of turkey with salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Pour gravy over all.
Combine remaining crumbs, milk and eggs.
Spread over the top of the casserole and dot with butter. Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Blend peanut butter and shortening in large mixer bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Shape into balls.
Roll into sugar.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put kisses on. Makes 4 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Add flour mixture gradually to oil mixture and fold in 3 large grated apples and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Bakes in 9 x 13 greased pan at 350° preheated oven for 60-70 minutes.
Last 5 minutes of baking, sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/2 tsp cinnamon mixture.

title: blueberry quick bread
directions: About 4 hours before serving or day ahead:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan (or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans; bake 65 to 75 minutes).

title: granny's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, chocolate and milk in a heavy bottomed saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; put in butter and vanilla.
Beat with spoon to remove shine from mixture. Pour into buttered platter and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Tie spices in cheese cloth.
Stir sugar into cider in large saucepan.
Add spices and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove spices and stir in orange and lemon juice, continuing to heat until served. (Can be prepared in crock pot.)

title: melvin's trail mix
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.

title: corn relish
directions: Chop all very fine, except corn (cut if off cob).
Boil all together for 30 to 40 minutes.
Put in jars.
A little turmeric added before removing from stove will make relish yellow.

title: chicken breast with bacon
directions: Form cheese into 1/2 size of walnut.
Wrap 1/2 chicken breast around each cheese ball.
Then wrap 2 slices bacon around each breast.
Cover as much as possible.
Secure with toothpick (remove after baking).
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter; add onion.
Add beaten eggs to cream.
Add salt and nutmeg.
Mix all ingredients with corn.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: fresh squeezed lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and cold water.
Mix well. Chill.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon slices and fresh mint sprigs.
Yields about 7 1/4 cups.

title: squash palermo
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese and garlic together and set aside. Oil an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with 3 tablespoons olive oil. Layer bread crumbs and squash in dish, starting with crumbs and ending with crumbs on top. Drizzle the rest of the olive oil on top of ingredients in dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, covered. Remove cover and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix together the ground turkey, chopped onion and green pepper.
Add bread crumbs and egg, enough to keep everything together.
Press into bottom and sides of 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Put prepared dressing into center of dish. Pour soup over top of dressing, covering completely.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix and form into patties.
Brown in margarine.

title: orange dream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, orange juice and oranges.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese and sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage in medium skillet, stirring until crumbly. Drain sausage on paper towel, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings. Saute onion and green pepper in reserved drippings in skillet for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix flour and cheese in bowl.
Stir in sausage and sauteed vegetables.
Spoon into pie shell.
Combine eggs, evaporated milk, parsley flakes, garlic salt, seasoned salt and pepper in bowl; mix until smooth.
Pour over sausage mixture. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown and set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter	bread
and
place, buttered side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Using half of the ham, make a layer over bread.
Using
half
the
cheese,
repeat.	Beat
together the eggs,
milk
and
mustard and pour over layers and refrigerate overnight.	Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: continental chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in the white wine at least 2 hours or as long as overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade; broil 5 minutes on each side.
Place chicken in lightly greased baking dish so each piece lies flat.
Mix Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Top each piece with cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Grease muffin tins and fill almost to top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: pecan - cheese ball
directions: Cut cheese and onion into chunks and grind.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix and chill.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken breast. In a large bowl mix sour cream, the chicken and celery soups, chicken broth, water chestnuts and chicken that has been cut into pieces.
Line bottom of a casserole dish with butter and Ritz crackers; pour the other mixed ingredients on top of crackers.
Put more crushed crackers on top.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for 5 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Beat eggs with water until light.
Add sugar and mix well. Add sifted ingredients.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
While warm, frost with orange butter frosting.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: ranch pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix in saucepan 1 cup brown sugar, water and butter; boil 5 minutes.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Mix in bowl 1 cup brown sugar, milk, Bisquick, raisins or dates, nuts and vanilla.
Spoon batter on top sugar mixture.
It will sink into liquid and spread out as it bakes.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve warm with plain or whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: italian grand cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
In another bowl, blend until smooth: Ricotta cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Pour this mixture on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a small amount of shortening in Dutch oven.
Pour cranberry sauce over chops.
Cover with soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: zucchini sweet chunks
directions: Large zucchini are best, 3 to 4 pounds each.
Cut zucchini squash in chunk pieces (do not peel).
Cut onions in half, then slice.
Put in large kettle and pour salt over squash.
Let set while you mix the syrup.
Mix all other ingredients in another pot and bring to a boil.
Stir well to mix sugar.
Pour over squash and onions and boil about 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir often.
When squash looks transparent, pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Blend soup, cheese and eggs.
Add milk and mayo.
Stir in broccoli.
Pour in dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes (longer if doubling recipe).

title: caramel filling
directions: Mix sugar, milk
and oleo in saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook	for 2 or 3 minutes.
Set off heat while testing
a
small
amount
in
a
saucer.
When the mixture clings to the
side of spoon, spread on 3 regular cake layers.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not add any other moisture.
Bake in oiled pan 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange balls
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix like a pie crust.
Put rind with dry ingredients.
Make a hole in the dough and put in eggs and juice.
Dough should be soft like a pie crust.
If more liquid is needed for dough, milk may be added.
Roll into small balls for they get bigger while baking.
Bake at 300° to 375° until brown. Frost, leave plain or cover with chocolate jimmies.

title: onion beef macaroni casserole
directions: Brown ground beef. Stir in soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in cooked macaroni and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese delight dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use mixer at low speed.
You can make into a ball.
Reserve 1 cup pecans and roll mixture in them. Serve with Ritz or Town House crackers.

title: reduced fat carrot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients, then beat 2 minutes at high speed. Pour into a Pam-sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool and frost with Fat-Free Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: corn pone
directions: Mix together and bake at 400°.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in fat.
Thinly slice garlic; sprinkle with salt and mash thoroughly to pulp.
Add to beef with onion, green pepper and chili powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add tomatoes.
Combine rice and beans in 2-quart casserole dish. Add hot beef mixture.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato supreme
directions: Boil potatoes ahead of time, with peelings on (night before). Peel and grate potatoes and cheese.
Add sour cream, onion tops, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Bake in uncovered casserole dish for 35 minutes or until light brown at 350°. Serve immediately.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Roll in small balls and press flat with fork.
Cook on ungreased pan for 10 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the other ingredients.
Chill and enjoy.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet; drain off excess fat. Add tomato soup and drained green beans. Simmer 10 minutes. Top with freshly mashed potatoes and sprinkle with grated Velveeta cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Thaw Cool Whip at room temperature.
Melt Hershey bar in microwave or in double boiler.
Add to Cool Whip, stirring to mix. Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 2 hours or more.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out into balls, then roll in powdered sugar to coat.

title: fluffy casserole
directions: Cube bread, shred cheese and beef.
Use part of oleo to grease 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Layer: bread, beef and cheese.
Repeat layers at least twice.
Beat eggs into milk and pepper.
Pour over layers and dot with remaining oleo.
Set in refrigerator several hours before.
Also can be made up the night before.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet sour sauce
directions: Blend cornstarch with sugar, lemon and orange peel, then with pineapple juice and vinegar.
Cook over low to medium heat until thick and clear.

title: fizz cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: bean bake
directions: Mix with 1 (11 ounce) can baked beans (do not drain).
Combine the onions and beans in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour with bacon on top.

title: old-fashion cream pie
directions: Mix in blender.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° until thickened.

title: delicious salmon casserole
directions: Parboil potatoes and pepper.
Drain salmon and flake into large pieces.
Add potatoes, peppers, parsley, pimento, eggs and olives.
Mix lightly.
Over mixture, pour cream sauce and sprinkle with bread crumbs, then with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: california barbecued steak
directions: Put steak in a plastic food bag.
If using flank steak, score top diagonally
on
both
sides.
Combine
catsup, chili sauce, soy sauce, honey, hoisin sauce, if using, green onions, garlic, salt and pepper
in
a
small
bowl;
mix
well.
Pour mixture into bag with
steak.
Fasten securely with wire tape. Place bag in a
shallow
pan.
Let marinate in refrigerator 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Lift
steak out of marinade, pat with paper toweling.
Broil
inches
from
heat,
brushing several times with marinade,
about 8 minutes on each side for rare for sirloin and 5
minutes each side for flank steak.
If doing on grill put steak
inches
from
grayed coals and do same amount of time.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes in lightly greased pan.

title: pantry pork chops
directions: Whisk together all of the ingredients, except pork chops, to make a marinade.
Pour the marinade into a large plastic resealable bag and add the chops.
Press the air out of the bag and seal it tightly.
Turn the bag several times to distribute the marinade.
Refrigerate for 20-30 minutes for best flavor.
Remove the chops from the marinade and grill over direct high heat for 10 minutes.
Turn once halfway through grilling times.
Remove from grill and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with grill roasted peppers and zucchini, if desired.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Mix raisins with boiling water.
Stir and set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and pork and beans until beans are broken.
Add flour and rest of dry ingredients to bean mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drain raisins and add, stirring to mix well.
Pour batter into 3 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Some people bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Also, some people use 2 loaf pans not 3.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer and put mayonnaise and bacon bits on top; do not toss until ready to serve.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix beef, 1/3 cup of tomato sauce, olives, onion, oats, egg and seasoning.
Spread in heavy 10-inch skillet. Cover with remaining 2/3 cup tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove excess fat from skillet before serving.
Cut in wedges to serve.

title: mary's dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Divide in 2 portions.
You may roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge beef cubes in flour mixture, reserving remaining flour.
In Dutch oven, brown meat in hot oil, turning often.
Add onion, water and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir tomatoes with liquid into reserved flour; add to meat with mushroom steak sauce, basil, celery salt and cayenne.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add potatoes; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally; add more water as needed.
Stir in mixed vegetables.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind onions, cabbage, tomatoes and peppers.
Add 1/2 cup canning salt and let stand overnight.
Run cold water through it.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in heated water.
Add reserved juices and other ingredients.
Congeal overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with turkey, chicken or ham.

title: sweet pastry
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Cut the butter into the flour mixture until it looks like coarse meal.
Add the lightly beaten egg and the vanilla.
Work until mixture will form a ball.
If dry, add 1 or 2 teaspoons water until dough is manageable.
Knead 5 or 6 times on counter.
Form 3 balls.
Wrap and chill.
(Pastry can be refrigerated a week before using or frozen for 3 or 4 months.)

title: a favorite rice dish
directions: Mix sour cream and milk.
Layer rice, cheese, sour cream and chiles in casserole.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: *Slice carrots about 3/8-inch thick.
Cook approximately 5 minutes in salted, boiling water until just tender.
Drain.

title: hamburger cheese pie
directions: Lightly grease 2 (8-inch) pie plates.
Cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain and add salt and pepper.
Spread evenly into pans.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beef and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: rye krisp squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place 1 tablespoon on each cracker.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
May be frozen and baked when ready to serve.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, margarine and walnuts; mix well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish; press down.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.
When cool, mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip; mix well.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk; beat until firm.
Place on top of other layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade fudge sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and cinnamon. Add cream and milk and mix well.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.
Yields 3 cups.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: In a double boiler, combine chocolate chips and condensed milk.
Let chips melt completely, stirring mixture well.
When the mixture is smooth, place saucepan with mixture in refrigerator and let chill until mixture is firm enough to roll into balls.
Roll in your favorite decoration or leave plain.
Makes about 30 (1-inch) truffles.

title: "day out" pot roast
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce and cranberry sauce.
Pour over roast in roasting pan.
(A slow cooker or crock-pot may be used.)
Put vegetables on top of roast.
Cover and cook in 200° to 250° oven all day.
Beef may be frozen when started.
No browning or seasoning is necessary.
If desired, at end of cooking time, meat and vegetables can be removed, sauce heated to bubbling and noodles cooked right in the gravy.
The longer this cooks, the more tender the meat.
Just turn it on and spend the day out.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla; beat well.
Add sugar, walnuts and crackers; mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan to make crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°; cool down.
Spread large Cool Whip on top of crust and top with cherries.
Keep cool until serving.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies; do not remove middle.
Reserve 3 crushed cookies for top.
Mix rest with butter.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.

title: chinese noodle crispies "spiders"
directions: Melt chocolate and caramel chips over hot, not boiling, water. When melted, stir in noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken in a large pot and cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and skim off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover pot; reduce heat and simmer gently 2 or 3 hours.
Soup may be strained before serving.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Heat applesauce and add to Jell-O to dissolve.
Cool for a few minutes. Add pineapple and 7-Up.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water, butter and oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Then add sugar, brown sugar, eggs, flour and cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in long cake pan.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado and mash with fork in a mixing bowl.
Blend in garlic.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Blend in onion. Using slotted spoon, blanch tomato in boiling water; remove and peel off skin.
Finely chop tomato and add to avocado mixture. Add chili pepper; blend thoroughly.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in pot but 1/2 of the water and cornstarch.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Mix water and cornstarch and add to pot.
Simmer for 3 more minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine beans.
Brown ground beef, drain and add to beans. Combine brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and catsup.
Add to beans. Cut bacon in chips.
Add to beans.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 casseroles.
Freezes great.

title: black bean soup(healthful eating)
directions: In a medium stockpot, simmer chicken broth, garlic, onion, celery and seasonings 1 hour.
In a blender or food processor, puree 1 can of the black beans; add to stockpot.
Stir in remaining 2 cans beans and heat through.

title: dirt
directions: Put the cookies into a zipper style plastic bag. Close the bag tightly.
Use a rolling pin to crush the cookies until they are as fine as "dirt."
Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into cups. Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture. Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Plant gummy worms or other candy creatures into the cups of "dirt."

title: southern spoon read
directions: Mix salt and cornmeal; add shortening.
Pour boiling water over and mix well.
Break egg into hot mixture and mix well; add milk into which baking powder has been mixed.
Mix all well and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 400°; serve with lots of butter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: thanksgiving leftover casserole
directions: Chopped turkey and dressing are mixed with leftover vegetables.
Add enough cooked noodles with dried instant soup mixes.
Add mushroom soup and enough gravy so mixture, when mixed all together, is moist.
I have even added red pepper, green pea pods and corn.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling water for 5 minutes, drain. Combine soup and sour cream, fold in drained squash and onions. Combine stuffing mix and butter.
Spread half the stuffing mix in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture on top, then spread on the remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven steak stroganoff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using 9 x 13-inch pan lined with aluminum foil, cut meat.
Add salt and pepper.
Place the onion on meat.
Layer potato slices and arrange mushrooms on top.
Mix the soup, sour cream, catsup, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a bowl and spread over top of pan ingredients.
Now wrap with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries through food chopper.
Mix sugar and pour over cranberries.
Let stand all night in refrigerator.
Add the marshmallows, pineapple, nuts and strawberry gelatin.
Mix all together and chill. Serve.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix baking mix, milk, and cheese until a soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: meatballs with creamy paprika sauce
directions: Mix together the turkey, oat bran, ketchup, pepper and garlic. Shape into small balls.
Fry in a nonstick pan sprayed with Pam. Remove the balls when brown.
Add the chicken bouillon to the pan along with the sliced onions.
Bring to a boil and simmer until the onions are tender.
In a separate bowl, slowly blend the evaporated milk into the 1/4 cup of flour until smooth.
Then slowly drizzle the chicken bouillon and onions and blend.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Add paprika.
Pour over meatballs.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift and mix all dry ingredients.
Add onion and beaten eggs. Pour hot water over this mixture, stirring until batter is smooth. Drop by spoon into hot fat about 350° until brown.

title: pineapple cool whip pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add large carton Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Mix all together and place in the pie crusts. Make ahead and freeze.
Take out 30 to 40 minutes before serving (serves 12 to 14).

title: cold bean salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all beans, pimiento and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Stir well and pour over bean mixture, tossing gently.
Cover; refrigerate to chill and blend flavors.
Stir gently several times before serving (if you remember).
Can be made day before.
Makes 10 servings.
Has appeared at potlucks at campgrounds across the country on our RV travels.

title: dot garnett's vegetable salad
directions: Drain all water from canned vegetables.
Mix all ingredients well and then mix the salt, pepper, sugar, oil, vinegar and water. Pour over the vegetables.
Lightly mix again.
Let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: sticky nut buns
directions: Tear 1 loaf thawed bread into irregular pieces and place in buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle the mixture of brown sugar, pudding, butter and cinnamon over bread pieces.
Tear up the second loaf the same way and layer on top.
Cover with a wet towel and let rise about 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside down immediately.
Nuts and raisins may be added with the brown sugar mixture layer.

title: punch
directions: Heat 3 or 4 cups water to dissolve sugar and jello.
Add remaining water.
Add 2 cans lemonade, diluted by directions.
Add 1 can undiluted.
Add pineapple juice.
Pour into containers and freeze.
Remove 5 hours before using and add ginger ale at serving time.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oil to 300° in 13 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Add potatoes and onions, stir, mixing well.
Sprinkle celery salt, lemon pepper and salt over potatoes.
Stir, mixing well.
Sprinkle onion salt over potatoes.
Continue to stir, mixing well.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large skillet.
Over high flame, stirring constantly until mixture becomes rather smooth and light in color, turn off flame.
Add baking soda, stirring constantly. Immediately transfer to greased cooking sheet, allow to cool, then break into small pieces.
One batch makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Grind onions and peppers.
Put all ingredients in large pot. Use about 1/2 can water for each can used to rinse.
Cook uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: In 3-quart casserole place oil, butter and onions.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 4 minutes until hot.
Stir in and mix well green pepper, cabbage, carrots, green onions, broccoli, cauliflower and celery.
Microwave at High, covered, for 4 minutes.
Add meat and mushrooms and continue to microwave, uncovered for 4 to 6 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mystery rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Mixture will be thick.
Spoon into greased, large muffin cups (6).
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: "sweet pea" salad
directions: Drain peas. Mix eggs, onion and salad pickles. Fold in peas. Place mayonnaise and mustard on top. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Fold together until mixed. Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef
in large skillet until meat is brown. Discard drippings and
add	chili powder, cumin and salt; cook 10 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda, clove, cinnamon, allspice and salt; set aside.
Cream butter; add sugars and mix well.
Add eggs, applesauce and buttermilk and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well; stir in nuts and raisins and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: 29 peppercorn dip
directions: Blend peppercorns, garlic, mustard and anchovies and their oil in blender.
Add 1 egg and blend 1 minute, then slowly blend in 1 cup oil.
Repeat process with remaining egg and oil.
Serve with crisp, raw vegetables.
Full recipe make 3 cups dip.
Very good. Kids love this one.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour dry pudding mix over undrained pineapple; mix.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Slowly fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: heath toffee bar coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, margarine and sugars.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture.
To the remainder, add the buttermilk, soda, egg, vanilla and 1/2 cup of chopped toffee bars.
Blend well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add muffin mix to corn mixture.
Then add rest of ingredients, except sour cream and grated cheese.

title: tea garden salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot tea.
Add cup of juice from mandarin oranges and pineapple. (Add regular orange juice to fill cup if needed.) Stir.

Place gelatin in refrigerator until it has thickened considerably. Drain and cut water chestnuts into small slices. Add chestnuts, pineapple and orange sections to gelatin. Spoon mixture into well oiled molds.
Refrigerate until set.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Chop the seasoning and lightly fry in butter or margarine. Add crab meat and mix well.
Add all but 3/4 cup of crumbs to mixture and 1/3 cup of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff crab shells or place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over stuffed crabs or casserole and place a small pat of butter on top. Bake for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, soda and salt in one bowl. Cream butter on low for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and beat for 2 minutes.
Add brown sugar and beat 2 minutes longer.
Add eggs, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and chips.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden.
Transfer off cookie sheet after 2 minutes.
Cool completely and store.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, eggs and oil; add flour mixture, nuts and carrots.
Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Put in two greased cake pans.

title: miss mary's famous chicken with pastry
directions: Place chicken in 3 cups of water with onion, celery and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Cook until tender over medium heat.
When tender;
remove chicken from broth and debone.
Cut into large chunks and place in the bottom of a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Remove
celery
and	onion
from broth.
Blend 4 tablespoons of
flour
with
1/4 cup water and gradually whisk into simmering broth.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened. Season with
salt
and pepper.
Pour enough sauce over chicken to just
cover.
Preheat
oven
Combine 2 cups flour with 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut shortening into flour with a pastry blender
or	fork
until mixture resembles cornmeal. Sprinkle with water; mix until
it	holds
together
and
forms a ball. Roll out on floured
board
to
about 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into strips and place
over
chicken.
Bake
until
pastry has browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried rice oriental
directions: Brown vegetables in 1/2 stick of margarine until tender.
Cook 2 cups of Minute rice; add to vegetables with 1/4 cup of soy sauce.
While this is warming, fry 2 eggs.
Mash very fine, then add to rice and vegetables.
(This freezes beautifully.)

title: strawberry parfait pie
directions: Defrost strawberries and drain.
Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add ice cream and dissolve.
Refrigerate until thick.
Beat with spoon and fold in strawberries.
Pour in graham cracker shell.
Chill.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand until well blended.
Do not use blender.
Pour into a large greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Very good!

title: ham dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut chicken livers in half.
Saute slightly with butter, soy sauce and garlic salt to taste.
Fry bacon slices slightly.
Take 1 chicken liver, 1 water chestnut and wrap strips of bacon around them.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place under broiler until bacon is crisp, turning once.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent dough and press into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Be sure to press seams together.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on crust.
Finely chop vegetables and gently mix in bowl.
Press onto cream cheese to form top layer.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: pumpkin gingerbread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine, sugar and orange peel.
Beat with an electric mixer on high speed until smooth.
Add egg whites, one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each addition.
Mix in pumpkin, corn syrup and molasses on medium until smooth.
In a small mixing bowl stir together sifted cake flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Gradually beat the flour mixture into sugar mixture, beating until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack in pan about 15 minutes.
Dust with sugar.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cover each half breast with cheese slices, then ham, and secure with toothpicks.
Saute the chicken in butter for 10 minutes, then put in casserole.
Put milk and soup in saucepan and heat over medium heat.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Add 1/2 cheese. Salt and pepper to taste. Place in 9x13 casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cheese and bread crumbs. Bake 350° for 45 min.

title: rice krispies bars(a "must try")
directions: Boil sugar and syrup in pan (careful not to burn) just until it bubbles.
Add peanut butter, then Rice Krispies.
Press into large pan (buttered).
Melt chips over double boiler; frost bars.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend in oatmeal, corn flakes and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudgy no-bakes
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and vanilla.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper, flatten with fingers.
Cool completely.
Makes sixty cookies.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix the first 3 items.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.
Add Certo; mix thoroughly.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: pizza burger
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Add olives and pizza sauce.
Put mixture on homemade buns.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap individually in foil.
Put in freezer. Take out as many as you need at a time and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel, cube and cook about 5 medium size potatoes.
In another saucepan heat cream of mushroom soup.
Add can of milk, onion dip mix and mild Cheddar cheese to thicken.
Stir in potatoes.

title: sour cream-coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions (in 2 cake pans).
Cool on rack and cut each layer in two, making 4 layers.
Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Reserve 1 cup.
Put the rest between the layers.
Mix the 1 cup reserved mixture with Cool Whip and ice the cake.
Put in an airtight container and refrigerate for 4 days before serving.

title: kummer special
directions: Brown meat in 12-inch skillet (do not drain).
Mix in onion; heat for 5 minutes on medium-high, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms, lower heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add SpaghettiOs, mix,
reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place the asparagus in buttered casserole (saving juice). Make sauce of the butter and flour.

Stir together until smooth. Add drained asparagus juice and cook until mixture begins to thicken. Add the cheese. Continue to cook until cheese melts. Pour sauce over asparagus. Sprinkle with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for a few minutes, until browned.

title: honey and nut tasteeos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cereals and 1/4 cup walnuts.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well (batter will be stiff).
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup walnuts.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean and top is lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36.

title: sally's cheese spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream, salt, onions and mustard.
Add grated Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate if not to be used soon. Flavors blend better if made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Allow to soften before serving as it is easier to spread.
Serve with Melba toast or other crackers.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix well.
Pour one half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Combine raisins, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the cinnamon mixture onto the batter in the pan.
Pour the remaining batter into the pan, sprinkle with the remaining cinnamon mixture.
Swirl a knife through the batter to slightly mix.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Combine the powdered sugar, vanilla and milk and pour over cake while hot.
Cake can be warmed in a microwave oven or refrigerated overnight and baked in the morning.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and peanut butter; gradually beat in eggs, sugar, flour mixture. Add vanilla.
Form into a roll; wrap in a heavily oiled paper and place in the refrigerator several hours.
Cut in thin slices; place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderately hot oven, 375°, for about 12 minutes.

title: hilmer's pumpkin pie(makes two 9-inch pies)
directions: Mix together and pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix all wet ingredients together.
Separately mix all dry ingredients together.
In a large bowl combine wet and dry ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool and then frost.

title: mother's lettuce dressing
directions: Mash the egg yolks and stir in other ingredients. Blend well and add the chopped egg whites. Toss over the broken lettuce.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Combine oil, corn, garlic, eggs and cornmeal.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 chilies and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain in cold water.
Chop vegetables and add vegetables and dressing to spaghetti.
Chill for one hour.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot or microwave.
Cook until cheese is melted. Stir and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring
sugar,
salt, milk and chocolate to a boil.
Add Karo and
oleo.	Cook
over medium heat until soft ball stage, stirring often.
Remove
from
heat.
Add
vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour in greased platter.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: zucchini sauté
directions: Cook onions in oil until transparent, stir frequently.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Cover pot and cook over low heat, stir but carefully until zucchini pieces are transparent, but still firm, This might take 10 to 15 minutes.
Can add a small amount of drained tomatoes liquid if vegetables are not very juicy.
Put cooked zucchini in oven proof dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler until cheese get brown.
Do not over cook zucchini, it should be firm and crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Fry bacon and lay on paper to drain. Fry onion and lay on paper towel to drain. Fry celery and lay on paper towel to drain. Fry okra and lay on paper towel to drain. In a large pot, put the tomatoes and can of water and set heat on high. When water starts to boil, add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, marjoram, basil, thyme and a shake of the hot pepper sauce. Bring to a boil for about 5 minutes. Add bacon, onion, celery and okra. Cook for about 30 minutes on low boil. Now add the shrimp, crab, fish or any other seafood you desire. Bring to a boil. Turn heat down to a simmer. Cook for at least one hour. The longer the better. Serve over hot white rice.

title: the preacher's corn bread
directions: *You may use 1/4 jar of jalapeno peppers, chopped.

title: horseradish crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine softened cream cheese, crabmeat, onion, mayonnaise, milk, horseradish and salt; mix well.
Pour into a small oven-safe serving dish and bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from the oven and allow to cool to room temperature, about 15 minutes.
Makes about 1-1/4 cups dip.

title: italian meat ring
directions: Mix all ingredients except barbecue sauce and cheese in a 2-quart round dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 14 to 17 minutes.
Top with 1/4 cup barbecue sauce and cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, on Medium-high for 2 to 4 minutes.
Let it stand 5 to 6 minutes.

title: summer salsa
directions: Dice veggies and then mix together with cheese and salsa. Serve with chips.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Heat mushroom soup with water and set aside.
Layer potatoes, salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with onions and layer of shredded cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with top layer of potatoes.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle grated cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and continue baking for about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: party spread
directions: Mix mayo and cream cheese well.
Add pecans, olives, juice and dash of pepper; stir well.
Chill for 24 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Squash should be parboiled about 5 minutes before adding other ingredients.
Slice zucchini lengthwise, take out seeds (reserve). Brown hamburger, add tomatoes, centers from zucchini, beef broth, seasonings; let cook a few minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Lay squash flat in a dish; fill with above mixture.
Sprinkle grated Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes to melt.

title: broccoli with rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings.
Boil broccoli and drain.
Mix with soup and cheese.
Add onion and celery with drippings.
Stir in rice and season with salt, pepper, Tabasco and red pepper.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and sour cream.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: peanut-butter bread
directions: The day before serving:
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In medium bowl, with fork, mix flour, sugar, orange peel, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat milk, peanut butter, margarine and egg until wel mixed.
Stir peanut butter mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken stew and dumplings
directions: In a large pan, bring water, onion and celery to a boil.
Add bouillon cubes for flavor.
Slow simmer, add chicken cut up into bite size pieces.
Continue to simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook until carrots are tender.
Then add noodles; cook until done.
CHICKEN RICE SOUP IS MADE THE SAME WAY, EXCEPT ADD 3 CUPS COOKED RICE INSTEAD OF NOODLES.

title: quick company chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add sauce and chicken.
Brown on one side, turn and brown on other side.
Add juice, cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Remove cover; crispen slightly.

title: zucchini in a flash
directions: Coarsely grate zucchini.
In 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine oil and garlic.
Microwave on High 35 seconds.
Stir in zucchini and coat well.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes or until tender-crisp, stirring once.
Serves 4.

title: corn cornbread
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sour cream and egg; mix well.
Add both corns and corn bread; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Done when center is firm when shaken.

title: rice cabbage goulash
directions: Heat shortening in a large skillet.
Add meat, stirring occasionally, and brown until crumbly.
Add garlic and onion and cook 5 minutes more, stirring frequently to prevent over-browning.

title: strawberry delight punch
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart punch bowl, combine tea and water.
Set aside.
In blender container, combine strawberries, lemonade concentrate and sugar; process at high speed for about 15 seconds, or until smooth.
Pour into tea mixture; mix well.
Serve over ice with lemon slice, if desired.
Makes 15 (4-ounce) servings.

title: mocha brownie torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 round layer pans.
Blend dry brownie mix with water and eggs.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pans and bake for 20 minutes.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Remove from pans and place on cooling rack.
Cool completely.
Beat cream until thick; gradually add sugar and coffee.
Beat until stiff. Frost and fill with cream mixture.
Sprinkle with shaved chocolate.

title: lou nett's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale.
Freeze in gallon milk carton.
Take out a couple hours before serving; put in bowl and mash until mushy.
(Cut away milk carton when placing in bowl.)
Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture and serve.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich cookies
directions: Beat margarine and peanut butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well. Add egg substitute and vanilla; beat well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl.
Mix 1 jar chopped corned beef and chives with cheese.
Blend well.
Form into ball.
Cut 2nd jar of beef into small squares and place around formed cheese ball. Serve with crackers, any style.

title: meat sauce
directions: This recipe can be cut back in smaller proportions, if desired.

title: elaine's easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch or a cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured surface.
Knead 20 times.
Pat dough on bottom and up sides of pan with floured hands or roll into rectangle and place on cookie sheet.
Pinch edges of rectangle, forming 3/4-inch rim.
Cook and stir ground beef, onion, salt and garlic until beef is brown. Drain.
Mix tomato sauce and Italian seasoning.
Spread evenly over dough.
Spoon beef mixture evenly over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, green pepper and cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip and fold in fruits. Last, add crumbled cookies, reserving some crumbs for top.
Let set 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Place croutons in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup, milk and eggs. Place crumbled sausage on top of croutons.
Add egg mixture on top of sausage.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour.
Add cheese on top and let melt.

title: lancashire hot pot(i've used this alot on a chilly day.)
directions: Brown chops in 1 tablespoon butter in heavy skillet over brisk heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange chops, standing on end, in deep, covered 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Brown onions slightly over medium heat in skillet used for chops.
Spoon onions into center of baking dish.
Brown carrots lightly in skillet and add to pot.
Then add oysters if used.
Combine any fat left in pan with enough butter to make 3 tablespoons.
Blend with the flour and brown lightly over rather brisk heat.
Stir in stock and bouillon cubes and continue stirring until mixture thickens. Season with 1 tablespoon salt, 1/2 tablespoon pepper, the sugar, thyme, Worcestershire and sherry.
Pour over ingredients in casserole and top with potatoes.
Season potatoes with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 2 hours, or until meat is tender and potatoes are done.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 12 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma's persimmon pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten whole egg.
Press persimmons through colander.
Add soda to pulp.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add milk and flour alternately, beating until smooth. Bake slowly for 1 hour at 275° in greased Pyrex.

title: pineapple broiler cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and flour.
In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Add to first mixture and stir to blend.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before topping.

title: grape juice
directions: Heat grapes, sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until the pudding slightly thickens.
Add cream cheese, beat until mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line oblong pan with whole graham crackers; add pudding mix and continue to alternate layers, ending with graham crackers on top.
Cover with favorite chocolate frosting or chocolate fudge sauce.

title: pepperoni rigatoni
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Layer half the ingredients in the order listed in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: italian bows
directions: Mix oil, sugar and
wine, then eggs.
Then add flour, a little at a time.
Knead
dough then let it rest for about ten minutes. Roll dough as
thin as possible.
Then cut in strips and tie in a bow.
Fry
in
deep oil until golden brown.
Then sprinkle with 10x sugar or honey.

title: green rice
directions: Combine ingredients:
rice, broccoli, cheese, onion, black pepper, salt and Accent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mom's parmesan potatoes
directions: In Ziploc bag, combine Parmesan cheese, flour, salt and pepper. Melt butter in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Put quartered potatoes in Ziploc bag mixture and coat them. Place potatoes one by one in baking dish of butter. When all potatoes are coated and placed in baking dish, bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs; add Jell-O, then flour (one cup at a time), mixing well after each addition.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Can use any flavor of Jell-O.
These are easy and are good.

title: fruit salad for holiday crowds
directions: Cook pineapple juice, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cool.
Whip cream; add to juice mixture.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator.
Makes large salad.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute rice, onion and mushrooms in butter. Add consomme. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raw potato patties
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix. Cover bottom of skillet with 1/4 cup oil.
Using 1 1/2 spoons of the mixture, add patties to oil and brown on each side.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, white syrup and evaporated milk for 4 minutes. Add margarine after boiling.
Beat well.
Pour into greased pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: a man's dish
directions: Open can of tuna and empty into skillet (medium heat) or saucepan.
Heat tuna until hot and pour in beaten eggs.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until eggs are done.

title: loaded mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, covered with water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until tender. Drain and place in mixing bowl. Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper. Beat on low to medium speed until light and fluffy. Stir in 2 cups cheese, bacon and onions. Transfer to 3-quart dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Lightly brown sausage.
Mix cheese, sausage and Bisquick.
Roll in balls, 1 inch in diameter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Heat in 375° oven 10 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add flavorings. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter; add oil, 1/2 parsley, garlic powder, salt, cayenne and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently with butter mixture.
Arrange in skillet in single layer.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.

title: linda's peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches and sugar until hot.
Add a little water and cornstarch to thicken.

title: queso dip
directions: Brown meat.
Add to melted cheese and tomatoes.
Serve with chips and vegetables.

title: busy day casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or Pyrex dish, smash ground chuck (uncooked) in bottom of pan.
Mix both soups together in a bowl. Pour over ground chuck.
Layer cheese slices; then layer Tater Tots over this.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make a golden brown roux with flour and fat.
Add onions, bell pepper and celery to the roux and cook until tender.
Combine tomato sauce and water.
Add tomato sauce, salt, red and black pepper.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes before serving.
Add parsley, green onions and shrimp.
Cook 30 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: akara(bean cakes)
directions: Soak beans in water for 1 hour.
Rub briskly to remove skins. Grind beans in blender or processor with enough water to make consistency like cake batter.
Add remaining ingredients to bean mixture.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
Akara is best when served hot!

title: green bean casserole(serves 10 to 12)
