directions: Fry bacon; drain and break into small pieces.
Fry chopped onion in bacon fat until soft.
Remove 2 tablespoons bacon fat and add to tomato soup.
Combine soup, sugar, bacon and onion and pour over green beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be made ahead.
Men love this dish!

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with mixture of 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat in oil in large pot or Dutch oven.
Stir in 2 cups water, bouillon cubes, celery and onions.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Add carrots and potatoes.
Cover.
Simmer an additional 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice provencal
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken; cook over medium-high heat 6 - 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic.

title: parmesan cheese square
directions: Cut crust off of bread.
Dip first slice of bread in butter. Dip second slice in eggs.
Dip third slice in butter.
Stack all three in that order and cut into 6 squares.
Roll square in Parmesan cheese.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These can be frozen.
Yields about 66 squares.

title: tuna noodle crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water according to package directions; drain.
Melt shortening in large skillet; add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, pimento, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cooked noodles and tuna.
Place mixture in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and then applesauce.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Stir in alternately with water. Stir in walnuts.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong cake pan.
Cool, then frost as desired.

title: honey-whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve
yeast in 1/2 cup warm water
in
large
bowl. Stir in honey, shortening, salt, 1 3/4 cups warm water and the whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in
white flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead on
lightly
floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side
up. Cover and let rise in warm
place
until	doubled. Punch	down and divide into 2 loaves.
Put
in	greased
pans. Brush with melted oleo.
Let rise until double,
about 1 hour. Bake in 375° oven until loaves are deep golden brown and sound hollow when tapped, 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef; chop as browning.
Add onion; drain and set aside.
Using the 2 tablespoons oil, oil all sides of a casserole dish, then layer the following:
corn tortillas, ground beef, enchilada sauce and cheese.
Repeat process until all ingredients are used, ending with the cheese (do this as if preparing lasagne). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (until bubbling).
Remove and let stand a few minutes before serving.
May be served with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato on the side.
Spanish rice also makes a nice accent.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey applesauce
directions: Wash apples without peeling or coring; cut them into quarters. Place them in large saucepan; add water, cover and cook over medium low heat 20 minutes or until apples are soft, stirring occasionally.
Strain apples through colander; add honey.
Stir to blend.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: grilled mushrooms
directions: Thread mushrooms on skewers.
Combine butter, dill and garlic salt.
Brush over mushrooms.
Grill over hot coals for 10 to 15 minutes, basting and turning every 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: summer salad
directions: Break up lettuce.
Cut up onion. Fry and crumble bacon.
In a large bowl with a seal, layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese on top.
Mix mayo and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Spread on top. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: yellow tomato preserves
directions: Wash tomatoes and remove stems, but do not peel or slice. Combine all ingredients and water; bring to a boil and then simmer 2 hours or until thick.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 pints.

title: creole cakes
directions: Melt butter in large pan; add flour, then add milt slowly. Stir until thick.
Add crab meat, parsley and onions.
Add seasonings accordingly.
Let set at least 2 hours (if mixture is not thick enough to form, add bread crumbs).
Form into round patties and cover the outside with bread crumbs.
Top each round with a "pat" of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: deep-dish beef pie
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat over medium-high heat.
Brown half the meat in skillet.
Remove.
Add oil.
Brown remaining meat.
Return all meat to skillet.
Stir in onion, celery, carrots, turnip, tomato juice, thyme, salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and + cup water.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until meat is nearly tender.

title: hot sauce
directions: Combine and serve over cream cheese, or also good with ham. Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato-orange-apple casserole
directions: Remove skin from cooked sweet potatoes and slice potatoes 1/2 inch thick.
Peel, slice and core cooking apples.
In a buttered casserole dish, arrange layers of sweet potatoes and apples.
Dot each layer with butter, using about 1 tablespoon.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over each layer.
Pour orange juice over all.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and dot with additional tablespoon butter.
Place in oven again and bake 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, lemon
juice, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and salt until well blended. Add
eggs,	one
at
a
time, mixing well after each addition. Place crust on baking sheet; pour in filling.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in from tbe edge comes out clean.

title: mud bars
directions: Beat together sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg, beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt). Mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Line a 9-inch pan with foil.
Spread batter into it.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread remaining chocolate chips on it.
Allow to stand for a few minutes, spread with spatula.
Let cool until chocolate sets.
Cut into squares.
Makes 18 bars.

title: lemon supreme cake dessert
directions: Drain mandarin oranges, save liquid.
Mix cake mix, beaten eggs and mandarin liquid.
Fold in orange pieces.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and soda that has been sifted together.
Add sour cream and fold in thawed coconut.
Add almond extract.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat all together.
After well blended, chill.
Can be served with or without liquor.

title: crab mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water and lemon juice.
Dissolve over low heat.
Set aside.
Combine softened cream cheese, soup and onion.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add gelatin and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into well-greased 4 cup mold.
Chill 4 to 6 hours or until firm. Unmold on platter, garnished with lettuce.
Serve with crackers.

title: jamaal's 30 minute spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, garlic and pepper in 2 tablespoons oil separately in same frying pan.
Set aside in separate dishes.
Brown meat lightly, then add Prego; let simmer, stirring occasionally, approximately 10 minutes.
Add all sauteed ingredients.
Bring to a bubbling simmer.
Then turn down low until spaghetti is done. Serve meat sauce over spaghetti with garlic bread and a tossed green salad.

title: dinner in the oven!
directions: Place pork chops on tinfoil and season.
Slice potatoes and onion and place on tinfoil.
Salt and pepper.
Add corn.
Put a few teaspoons of butter on top.
Wrap up in foil.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: shrimp or crabmeat salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate.
Stuff 4 large tomatoes, or just use as a dip!!

title: minute fudge icing
directions: Put all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Stir and bring to boil, full rolling boil, and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
If it should get too thick, add 1 tablespoon cream.
Makes enough to frost 8-inch square loaf pan.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil and bay leaf; simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Add wine, water, salt and pepper; simmer another 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
If sauce is too thick, add more water.
When sauce is cooked, add cheese and mix well.
Serve over pasta.
Delicious. Serves 1 to 9.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and garlic in butter.
Stir in meat and brown. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add soup and stir.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle on parsley and serve over noodles or rice.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a flat glass baking dish in order listed.
Spread layers evenly.
If salad is not to be served at once, do not add bacon, but cover with foil and chill.
Add bacon at serving time.

title: corn pudding
directions: In a deep mixing bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Melt butter in deep baking dish.
Pour butter into corn mixture; mix well. Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Top and sides will be golden brown.

title: crisp baked chicken(fat:  3 grams per serving)
directions: Soak chicken in milk for 30 minutes.
Remove from milk; season with salt and pepper.
Roll each chicken breast in corn flake crumbs and set aside for 10 minutes.
Spray a baking dish with cooking spray and arrange chicken in dish.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: punch(refreshing!)
directions: Mix all in large punch bowl and enjoy.

title: potato skin casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add rice, soups, chopped onion, mushroom pieces and water into baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together and add salt and pepper to taste.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and remove foil.
Continue to bake for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill, serve.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Dice; place in buttered casserole. In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pinch of pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and cream.
Gradually cook over low heat until thick and smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with bread crumbs and rest of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: dirty penny bath(tarnish remover)
directions: Will need a saucepan, potholder, spoon, tarnished pennies and paper towel.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix
kraut, onion, sweet pepper, sugar and vinegar well and serve.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Core and quarter and chunk apples.
Mix in bowl with first 5 ingredients.
Mix together the next 4 ingredients in bowl. Mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Place in paper bag and seal bag.
Put in oven shelf farthest from heat. Place on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Peel and chunk potatoes; boil until they fall apart.
Cool in cold water; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except sliced egg. Mix together and cover top with sliced egg.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: baked nut rice(favorite recipe of mrs. white)
directions: Thin peanut butter with warm water to the consistency of thin cream.
Mix all ingredients.
The mixture should be quite thin. Bake in a hot oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is also a good filling for baked green peppers.
If used for breakfast, omit the onion.

title: hummus
directions: Put tahini, water, lemon juice and garlic in a blender. Add a little salt and pepper. Blend until smooth, adding a few beans at a time. Cover and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Heat squash in heavy skillet, adding water only if absolutely necessary.
Boil 5 minutes or until squash is tender.
Drain and mash squash thoroughly.
Add 1 cup bread crumbs, 1/2 cup cheese, salt, pepper, milk and eggs.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining bread crumbs and cheese and sprinkle on top.
Bake additional 10 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, baking powder, flour, salt and oil.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-banana delight
directions: Cover
bottom
of a 10 x 15-inch dish with sliced cake. Dissolve
the jello in the boiling water in a large bowl, then add frozen
strawberries,
stirring to break apart.
Sprinkle pecans and
place	bananas
over cake slices.
Pour jello and berries over all and refrigerate while mixing pudding according
to directions.
Pour pudding over jello and top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chimmy chongas
directions: In a large skillet add all the chimmy ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Cook until the beef is browned and is crumbled.
Place the cooked beef mixture inside of each of the tortillas and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up each tortilla with the ends tucked in.
Deep fat fry each of the tortillas until brown and crispy.
Remove and place a little garnish on each.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Then add eggs and mix.
Then add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Spray pie pan with Pam and bake on 350 degrees for about 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in oregano.
Stir in salt, pepper, onion, green pepper, bread crumbs and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Press into pie shell.

title: douglas jellyroll
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. In another bowl, beat sugar, egg yolks, milk and flour until fluffy. Add beaten egg whites. Fold in flavoring, baking powder and salt. Pour in pan that has been lined with paper and greased well. Bake at 350° until light brown. When done, remove from pan onto a dampened cloth sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Spread with jelly and roll up.

title: mud pie
directions: Press in 9 x 13-inch pan the first 3 ingredients.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Mix together next 3 ingredients. Put on top of crust after crust is cool.
Mix pudding.
Pour on top of 2nd crust.
Then top with the rest of Cool Whip.
Put nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon fish roll-ups
directions: Melt oleo, lemon juice and bouillon.
Heat slowly until bouillon dissolves.
In a medium bowl mix rice, broccoli, cheese and 1/4 cup lemon oleo sauce.
Divide among fillets.
Roll up and place seam side down in a baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over roll-ups.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with paprika.

title: milord(aristocratic and slimming quaff)
directions: Mix orange and lemon juices, bitters and soda water.
Pour into a glass and decorate with an orange twist.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Heat to boiling.

title: "dippin apples"
directions: Gather up several crisp apples.
Cut into slices.
Cream together above ingredients until smooth.
Then dip!

title: brown jug cheese soup
directions: Combine bouillon cubes, onion, water, potatoes and mixed vegetables in a Dutch oven. Simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add cream of celery soup and cheese, heat and stir until cheese is melted and soup is hot.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients; roll into balls and smash using smooth bottom of a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: crunchy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 12-inch pan.

title: marinade
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Add meat, turn to coat well. Cover refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Remove and grill, turning and basting with marinade.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 80 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cook until thick,
the eggs, flour, milk salt sugar and vanilla.
Put in layers starting with vanilla wafers-add pineapple, pour custard over layers.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: In large bowl, combine cocoa and margarine; beat until smooth. Add powdered sugar, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat in peanut butter until fluffy.
Spread over cupcakes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Take 1 pound frozen bread dough and thaw.
Flour and then roll with a rolling pin.
Beat egg slightly and brush on rolled dough. Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Distribute cut up, sauteed onion and mushrooms over surface.
Take fried bulk Italian sausage and sprinkle over ingredients.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, then shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Roll the dough like a jelly roll and brush outer side with beaten egg.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rices according to directions on package (do not overcook).
Melt butter in skillet and saute onions and celery. Add all ingredients to a 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Add meat.
Refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.

title: shrimp mozambique style
directions: First, put the olive oil, margarine and the garlic in a frying pan.
After that, put the shrimp in the frying pan.
Wait until the shrimp change color, then add the salt, hot sauce, parsley and 1/4 cup of beer.
Let it cook for 3 minutes and add the Goya; mix it well and serve it with fries or rice on the side.

title: date nut bread
directions: Put dates and sugar into a bowl; over this pour boiling water. Let cool.
Sift soda, salt and baking powder with flour.
Add nuts.
Add beaten egg.
Pour first mixture into flour and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake 45 minutes in medium oven.

title: banana pudding splits
directions: In blender, process yogurt on high speed for 30 seconds; add pudding mix and process for 1 minute, scraping down sides of container if necessary.
Cut each banana into 6 diagonal slices and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Arrange 2 banana quarters into each of 4 goblets or dessert dishes; top with 1/4 of the pudding mixture.
Sprinkle each portion with 1/4 of the pistachios; then top with 1 tablespoon whipped topping and add 1 cherry.
Each serving provides:
1/4 milk, 1/2 fat, 1 fruit and 60 optional.

title: mom's summer coolers
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed. Take 1 scoop of ice cream and drop it in a glass.
Spoon jello on top of ice cream. Repeat first two steps.
Drop one large spoon of whipped cream on top of your Jell-O.
Now add your sprinkles. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lucy johnson's peanut brittle
directions: Put 1/2 cup of water in a heavy skillet and boil.
Add sugar and syrup.
Stir until dissolved.
Boil until it spins a thread. Add peanuts and cook slowly over low heat until golden brown. Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and soda.
Stir quickly and pour while foaming on two buttered cookie sheets.
Let cool. Break apart and store in a dry place.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, mustard, paprika, pepper and garlic.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown ribs.
Put in oven. Baste with sauce.
Bake at 325°, covered or uncovered, until ribs are tender.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and flour in a saucepan and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and whip until fluffy.
Spread pineapple pie filling in uncooked pie shells until half full, then pour cream cheese mixture on top of filling.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 325° for 4O to 45 minutes.

title: sausage-cheese biscuits
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Add cheese.
Add Bisquick and sausage/cheese together with enough milk to make sticky.

title: homemade cream cheese
directions: Spoon yogurt onto the cheesecloth.
Tie cheesecloth at the top and hang the "bag" over a bowl to catch the whey.
After all the whey has drained (leave overnight), a firm ball of "cream cheese" remains.
Refrigerate.
Yields approximately 3 ounces.

title: pork chop potato casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place layers of potatoes, onion and cheese in greased casserole.
Combine mushroom soup, milk and seasonings in bowl; blend well.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Top with pork chops; cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: short ribs hungarian
directions: Sprinkle a heavy skillet with the salt.
Place short ribs, fat side down, in skillet and brown on all sides; drain off the excess fat.
Add onion and brown; combine remaining ingredients except sour cream, then pour them over ribs.
Cover and simmer slowly for 2 hours or until tender, adding more tomato juice if needed.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve with buttered noodles and poppy seeds; makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: raisin-pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Stir in raisins, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the sugar and flour.
In a heavy saucepan, combine the margarine, water and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar. Add the oil, sour cream, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well, then pour into a greased 11 x 16-inch jelly-roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until it tests done with a toothpick. While cake is baking, prepare the frosting.

title: rhubarb dream squares
directions: Mix like pie crust the flour, powdered sugar and margarine. Bake in an ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix the eggs, sugar, 1/4 cup flour, salt and rhubarb.
Pour over crust.
Bake for 35 minutes.
(Can sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top before baking.)

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies(just like your favorite sandwich)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl with electric mixer beat butter, peanut butter, brown sugar and honey until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until well combined. Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Using thumb or back of spoon, make 3/4-inch wide indentation in center of each cookie.
Fill each with about 1 teaspoon jelly.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden.
Remove immediately.
Cool on wire racks.
Yummy!

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: Mix together brown sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cool; stir in vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy after each addition of sugar.

title: jam bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs and water into mixture.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Add nuts and blueberries.
Mix gently.
Spray eight 1-pint, wide mouthed canning jars with nonstick cooking spray oil.
Then half fill jars with mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in jars at 325° for 45 minutes. Allow to cool slightly and
seal tightly with sterilized lids. When ready to serve, spoon out of jars.
Incredible.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oleo, cocoa, sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and let cool.

title: farmers-style vegetable soup
directions: Roast pepper in the broiler until skin is burnt and puffy. When cool enough to handle, peel. Discard seeds.

Dice pepper. Heat oil in a large saucepan. Saute leeks, onions and celery in oil until slightly softened. Add diced pepper and remaining ingredients through tomatoes. Stir in enough chicken broth to cover the vegetables by 1-inch. Bring to a boil. Add potatoes and cook over medium-low heat for 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Garnish with croutons.
Serve with a salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Make a sauce of the other ingredients.
Pour over broccoli in a casserole and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: broccoli, chicken and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in casserole dish until tender.
Add cooked, cubed chicken, butter and cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cookie sheet meatballs
directions: Mix everything together, except oatmeal.
Add oatmeal to make it all stick together.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until done.
This makes a lot of meatballs.

title: walnut chiffon cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Make a well and add, in order, oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Measure egg whites into large bowl along with cream of tartar. Beat until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over whipped egg whites, gently folding with rubber spatula just until blended.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over the top and fold in gently with a few strokes.
Pour into ungreased tube pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert until cool.
Frost with a butter frosting and sprinkle chopped nuts all over top.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour ingredients directly into freezer container.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: yellow punch
directions: Boil sugar and 1 cup water to dissolve jello and Kool-Aid. Mix all ingredients.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
Serves around 50.

title: lo-fat chicken
directions: Spread rice in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange salted and peppered chicken over the rice.
Add water.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° approximately 2 hours.

title: ri's nacho supreme
directions: Break taco shells into bottom of pan.
Spread beans on bottom. Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over beans.
Top with grated cheese, chopped tomatoes and black olives.
May also add shredded lettuce.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Combine eggs, onion and soup. Alternate layers of cooked broccoli, egg, soup mix, cheese and stuffing mix in 2-quart casserole.
Dot top layer with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: bob's best chili
directions: Brown meat and chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add the tomatoes, beans, onion and sauce.
Cook on simmer for 1 hour.

title: chocolate-peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Crush cookies and peanuts.
Whip all ingredients together, except topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze.
Before serving, drizzle with fudge topping.
Sinfully delicious!

title: cobbler
directions: Put flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in square baking pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch) and mix together.
Cut up margarine laying on top of dry ingredients fairly evenly.
Mix in enough milk to make a cake-like batter.
Lightly spoon fruit and juice over top and bake at 350° until done (about 45 minutes).
(It's done when crust comes to top and turns light brown.
Should still be juicy inside but not doughy.
Stick knife in middle and slightly pull apart to see and check for doneness.)

title: crunchy chicken bake
directions: Choice chicken parts (cleaned and excess fat removed); season heavily with Lawry's lemon pepper.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Chicken is crunchy and tasty with no frying!

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Add Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Place all mixed together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt down in oven at 350° until cheese appears watery, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Transfer to another dish.
Crush Ritz crackers on top and put chunks of butter on top.
Bake until crackers are golden brown and butter is melted at 350°.

title: new irish potato dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Put in a 4-quart kettle along with the water.
Add the salt and pepper, butter and milk.
Boil until potatoes are tender.
Roll biscuit dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares and drop into rapid boiling potato broth.
Cook dumplings 2 minutes.
Best served while hot.

title: chewy milk chocolate chunk brownies
directions: Stir the flour into dry mix.
Mix as directed using oil, water and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meat loaf with cheese-tato topping
directions: Mix milk with bread crumbs.
Beat in next five ingredients. Mix in ground beef with a fork.
Turn into a 9-inch pie plate. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: whopper cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Mix in eggs and peanut butter.
Add oats, baking soda, raisins and chocolate chips.
Use ice cream scoop.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes large cookies.

title: cinnamon "glass" candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients without stirring to hard crack stage (300° to 310°).
Add coloring and cinnamon oil.
Stir.
Pour into 2 oblong cake pans or cookie sheets (buttered).
Cool. Hit pan to crack in pieces.

title: roman apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and 2 teaspoons cinnamon together.
Mix all in first 5 ingredients.
Fold in apples.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with mixture of sugar, nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Blend in lemon juice, peel and butter. Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm topped with whipped cream.

title: dip dog batter
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Wipe off hot dogs and cover with batter.
Fry in deep vegetable oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: rice dish
directions: In skillet, brown onions and Spam.
Add celery and green peppers.
Mix eggs in separate bowl, then add to skillet and scramble with onion mixture.
Pour over cooked rice and flavor with soy sauce, salt and pepper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop onion and cook in 1 stick margarine until onion is transparent.
Mash squash with fork.
Combine onion and margarine with slightly beaten eggs.
Add soup, squash and bread crumbs. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Before last 10 minutes of baking, top casserole with Cheddar cheese and French fried onions.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Put nuts and cherries in bottom of tube pan.
Put brown sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Quarter biscuits and use 1/2 of them after shaking them in sugar and cinnamon.

title: hummus
directions: Blend beans until smooth.
Add other ingredients; blend until smooth.
Add bean liquid until mixture is consistency of dip. Chill.
Makes 1 cup.
Serve with pocket bread for dipping.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and cake mix together.
Follow directions on cake mix except use milk instead of water.
Bake in 2 round cake pans. After cake has cooled, split layers in halves so that you have 4 layers.

title: dave's good ole' egg sandwich
directions: Spray #5 skillet with Pam on medium heat.
Crack egg on edge of pan and slowly drop egg into pan.
Bust yolk with edge of spatula, be sure not to scramble the egg.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When egg has firmed up, flip once.
When egg is done, put egg on a napkin to soak up any oil.
Spread mayonnaise on the 2 pieces of bread.
Put egg between the bread and enjoy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix and bake in greased pan for 35 minutes at 325° to 350°. Use long pan.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Use 9 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch sheet cake pan. Layer cabbage, onions, potatoes and corned beef. Pour on celery soup mixed with water. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 400° in pan covered with foil.

title: homestead salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool frozen vegetables.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and kidney beans.
Stir sugar and flour in a saucepan.
Add vinegar and mustard and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix into vegetables while still hot.
Dash on salt and stir.
Cover well and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken tortellini soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven combine chicken broth, seasoning packet from vegetables, tortellini and hot pepper sauce. Bring to boiling.
Add vegetables.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and cook 5 to 7 minutes more or until tortellini is al dente (tender but still slightly firm) and vegetables tender.
Cook this simple, stir-together soup in less than 15 minutes.

title: cheese chocolate fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine on low heat, stirring occasionally. In large bowl, mix sugar and cocoa. Pour melted cheese and margarine into sugar and cocoa mix. Add vanilla and nuts; mix well. Pour quickly into greased 9 x 13 pan. Chill until firm.

title: spud's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In mixing bowl, mix sugar, eggs, and cornstarch. Add syrups, butter, and vanilla. Mix thoroughly. Place pecans in bottom of pie crust and pour filling over. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop surprise
directions: Brown pork chops in oil and drain.
Place in a large skillet or casserole.
Cover with beans, rice and sauerkraut, then pour tomato sauce over all.
Simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour in 350° to 400° oven or on top of stove, covered with lid.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Pour dressing over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix pudding as directed on boxes.
Crush Oreos into little pieces.
Mix the Cool Whip and the sour cream together.
Start with thin layer of Oreos on the bottom of the pan.
Then spread a layer of the pudding.
Then spread the cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Then layer again with cookies.
Follow these steps until all the ingredients are gone.

title: linguine with broccoli
directions: Cook linguine until al dente; drain.
Saute garlic in olive oil for 1 minute.
Add scallions and broccoli, stirring to combine. Pour chicken stock over mixture and cover.
Cook for 2 minutes or until tender, but still bright green.
Add basil, then toss with linguine and Romano cheese.
Season with hot pepper flakes, if desired.

title: kisses
directions: Add salt and cream of tartar to egg white and beat very stiff.
Beat in 1/4 cup powdered sugar and fold in remaining sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased paper on a pan.
Dust with powdered sugar and bake in a slow oven (275°) about 50 minutes increasing the heat to brown slightly.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
In a large stew pot, combine all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Good to munch on all day.

title: oven fried eggplant
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Peel eggplant, slice 1/4-inch thick.
Brush both sides of eggplant with mayonnaise.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Bake on a lightly greased baking sheet at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: beefaroni casserole(this is good and easy)
directions: Cook ground beef with celery and onion until beef is done. Drain off all grease.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper and stir well.
Cut heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain well.
Combine macaroni, sauce and 1 cup cheese and mix well.
Put in casserole dish and top with other 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until bubbly and cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach and nuts salad
directions: Mix the spinach and nuts gently in a bowl. Set aside.
Blend all the ingredients except bacon bits. Toss dressing in salad. Serve immediately, sprinkled with bacon bits.
Serves 4.

title: sliced cucumber pickles
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Cook to boiling point. Add peeled cucumbers and onions.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from fire and place in jars.

title: chocolate plunge (dipping chocolate)
directions: Microwave corn syrup and cream in a large microwavable bowl on HIGH 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture comes to boil. Stir in chocolate until completely melted. Serve warm as a dip with fresh fruit, cookies or pretzels. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crunchy breakfast bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, coconut
and walnuts in bowl.
Blend brown sugar, butter and honey in
a small bowl.	Add to oat mixture; mix well. Press into a greased 9 x
13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut	into
bars.
Yield: 2 dozen bars.

title: barb's easy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken breasts in shallow glass bowl.
Add chicken breasts and turn to coat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll chicken breasts in Italian flavored bread crumbs. Place in Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour over 1/4 cup melted butter and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until done and juices run clear.

title: meatball geneva
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup and apple juice.
Mix lightly.
Shape into bite size meatballs.
Brown on both sides. Place in baking dish.
Combine catsup and apple juice.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at
a
time.
Add whipping cream and flour, alternating.
Add
nuts and vanilla. Bake in a greased, floured tube pan for 1 hour
and 15 minutes at 325°.
Do not open oven during first hour.

title: elsie's chess pie meringue
directions: Stiffly beat the 2 egg whites and salt.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and a little vanilla.
Beat well and spread on cooked pie. Brown for about 12 minutes in a 360° oven.

title: stove top one-dish chicken bake
directions: Bring 2 cups of water and margarine to a boil. Add Stove Top stuffing and stir until moistened. Let stand for 5 minutes. Bring soup and soup can of water to a boil. Place chicken breasts into a 12 x 8 baking dish and pour soup over chicken. Top with Stove Top stuffing and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: mere mere joe's passion fudge
directions: Cook 1 cup sugar in black iron skillet over low heat.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon until sugar melts and is light brown in color.
Cook remaining 2 cups sugar with milk in a big pot over low
heat until it bubbles on side of pot.
Pour hot syrup mixture into pot of sugar and milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until firm ball stage. Remove from heat. Add soda, stirring well as it foams.
Add oleo. Stir until melted. Add vanilla. Beat until candy begins to thicken. Gently stir in pecans, then pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat bananas until liquid; add eggs and beat thoroughly. Cream sugar and butter; add bananas and eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour that has been sifted with salt, baking powder and soda. Stir, but do not beat.
Fold in nuts.
Place in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Place milk in double boiler and add marshmallows stir until melted.
Cool.
(I place ice in a large bowl and set the marshmallow pan inside to cool faster.)
Then add creme de menthe, creme de cocoa and a few drops of food coloring.
Keep pan in ice and stir until liquor is blended in.
Add well beaten whipping cream, fold and pour into pie crust.
Freeze.
Remove 15 mins. prior to serving.

title: oatmeal banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir to blend well.
Divide batter into two medium greased and floured loaf pans or one loaf pan and 12 muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (35 to 45 minutes for muffins and up to an hour and 10 minutes for loaves, depending on elevation and humidity.)

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Lightly grease a cookie
sheet with butter.
In a heavy skillet add all ingredients.
Bring
to boil over medium heat. With a wooden spoon
stir constantly until golden brown (about 6 minutes).
Spread in
buttered cookie sheet.
Pat until very thin. Let cool, then break in pieces.
Store in airtight can.

title: kahlua
directions: Put all ingredients into glass jar.
Ferment for 1 week. Shake frequently.

title: gumdrops
directions: Cut gumdrops into 4 or 5 pieces each and dredge with nuts in the 1/4 cup extra flour.
Cream egg yolks and sugar until fluffy. Stir in gumdrops, nuts and flour mixture.
Use fingers; mixture will be very stiff and crumbly.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in 1/4 at a time.
Amazing, but you have a batter.

title: sorghum cake
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients.
Then add dry ingredients. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Good with coffee.

title: sausage casserole(yields 60 servings)
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until tender. Wash and drain.

title: grandma sieffert's peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Add eggs. Mix baking soda with hot water and add to batter.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Shape into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Beat together the sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in flour until mixture is smooth.
(The batter will be stiff.)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until set and golden brown.
Cut into squares.
Makes approximately 40 squares.
